name: Vintage 1956 Trailer "Pinky"
host_about:
Happily married adventurers!
We like riding our bikes, paddling outrigger canoes, heli-skiing and great beer!
Can't live  without strong coffee and camping!
We have 2 cats that we spoil rotten, Fred and Ruby.
Rarely watch TV, but got hooked on Mad Men via Netflix! 
We dine out a lot (neither of us cook), don't have kids, and enjoy everything from Burning Man to 5 star hotels!
We frequent our outstanding LA museums, and see lots of shows.
We are architecture enthusiasts and love to go on tours through the MAK center where we often get to tour homes by amazing Mid-Century Modern architects like Lautner and Neutra.
We're from the Pacific Northwest and appreciate it, but live in Los Angeles working our tails off.
Looking forward to finding treasures on Air BnB!

name: Long Beach 50s Mod Bixby Bed/Bath
host_about:
A Philly native, Jean has lived in and around Los Angeles most of her life now.  

Jean can give you ideas what to explore and how to best navigate LA's crazy traffic patterns to get there...  from the best ocean views in Palos Verdes, the freshest seafood in San Pedro, to the Grammy museum at LA Live or the Getty on the Westside.  

A writer by trade, Jean spends most of her time -- well -- writing.

When she's not writing, she likes beach walks, tennis, urban hiking, and exploring the art and architecture of Los Angeles.  Especially the many mid-century modern rancho homes built by Cliff May, Edward Killingsworth, and Neutra.  

She knows the South Bay, Long Beach, San Pedro and greater Los Angeles like the back of her hand -- so if you want the best Thai in Hollywood, kimchi in K-town,  taco truck in Boyle Heights,  Ethiopian or Jewish Deli on Fairfax-- she can direct you!  

Jean's always on the hunt through the many vintage, antique and salvage stores in Long Beach and Orange for some unique 50's modern antiquarian item.

name: Plant Lovers Guesthouse Nestled in Tropical Pool Oasis
host_about:
I have the hardest time finding words to describe myself so instead, I'll share my beliefs :) I believe in love and beauty and find it in everything and everyone I come across. I cherish and treasure the simplest things. I believe that you can develop friendships with substance by becoming interested in other people than trying to get them interested in you. I believe in living unselfishly and genuinely. I believe that you are in charge of how you react to the people and events in your life. You can either give negativity, power over your life or you can choose happiness instead. Take control and choose to focus on what is important. I live to spread positivity like a disease :) 

My partner, Hollie, and I live in the main house (front house), detached from the studio. We love meeting our guests however we respect and provide complete privacy for our guests so we don't come out to the backyard space unless we're picking veggies from the garden.  However, if you'd like to meet, let me know upon booking so I will come out to introduce myself!

name: Weho Studio Duplex w/Prvt Patio-98% Walking Score!
host_about:
Writer who works partially from home, so I can often be flexible, with notice, on checkin and checkout (pending other reservations.) I have two small rescue dogs, but they stay to another side of the house for the most part (they're never allowed in your rental space except the patio area, so your room is dander free. But severe allergies or those with dog phobias might want to book elsewhere.

Respectful and friendly. I'm happy to  point you to the sites, and some only locals know about.  Or you can just go your own way every morning, explore the city for pleasure or work, and have a great, safe, friendly place to sleep or rest. 

For guests I especially welcome world travelers and anyone on business or vacation. This is NOT for longterm visitors nor for those looking to entertain within the unit. You have total privacy here and can come and go as you wish. The only time we run into one another is in the front door entryway, which is set off from both our parts of the house. 

You're an adult, I'm an adult, what you do is your business. Just as long as you're respectful and turn off lights, lock the front door, don't leave towels mildewing on the wood floor, treat the rental as it's someone's home and not an anonymous hotel, we will get along great! Literally had 300+ excellent guest experiences to date! (and about 3 not-so-excellent. I'm happy with that ratio. :)

name: Pasadena Foothills Oasis #1
host_about:
Greetings! I am a classical musician, with a definite appreciation for all the Fine Arts-
Raised and educated back-east, and loving the warmth and kindness of Southern Californians! Gardening with rare,tropical plants- and visiting local museums, are definitely high on my list... along with attending concerts, antique shops, and new restaurants in the area. I enjoy sharing my home with fellow travelers, who are looking to discover what a great place that Pasadena is!

name: Be Working from Here
host_about:
I have enjoyed becoming a veteran host on Airbnb, having hosted over 2000 guests in my home since 2013, many of them returning again and again. I have learned so many new things from my guests that have made my life richer: things about their hometown, recipes, new websites, things I would never have learned otherwise. I feel really blessed that some of the most terrific people in the world have chosen my home to stay in and to share their wisdom with me. 
I am of Indian descent; my parents immigrated to the US from South India, and I have lived in Los Angeles since I was 2-years-old.  My hobby is collecting "old" technology. I find it fascinating how quickly technology is changing.  I have a 1950 television, an antique record player, a camera, a telegraph machine, and a telephone in my collection. My favorite food is dark chocolate-- I have to have a bite a day! I love being a tourist in my own city, exploring all the special spots that most residents take for granted and never visit. I like learning the history behind a location, finding the best restaurants, and good movies and television!  When I visit a new city, it is important to me to stay in a spotless, ultra-comfortable place.  I love little luxuries, the best pancakes, the nicest sheets, the most comfortable pillow, the perfect cup of tea.  Things that irritate me when I travel are: getting lost and people that ruin my day with their not-friendly attitudes. Little details do matter, and I love making that difference for my guests.  I have worked as a tour guide, so I can give you those helpful hints that can make a huge difference when you are traveling.

name: Touch of Big Sur near Venice Beach
host_about:
Hi, I'm Paul.  
     I own and manage a small residential construction and remodeling firm here in the western region of Los Angeles.  I generally work close to home, which affords me the flexibility to meet most incoming guests.  
      I love the year- round ocean breezes in Mar Vista, a nice little community sandwiched between Venice to the west and north, Santa Monica to the north, Culver City to the east, and Marina Del Rey to the south and west.  All of these areas are just minutes away by bicycle, which is one of the best ways to see the beaches and surrounding areas.  There is a bike rental shop just blocks away.
      I have come to really love hosting -- I really enjoy meeting people from all over the world, and most guests have impressed me as truly wonderful people.  I also enjoy investing my time and income doing home improvements, so most things around the house and landscaping have had an aesthetic face lift.

name: Private Room in Elegant French Gothic Home
host_about:
I'm a writer, author, and have a PhD in film and theology from King’s College London. I was director of a film school for 13 years and now have a consulting business in the film industry. I love to eat my husband David’s amazing food, especially with good company. I love traveling and am adventurous, love strange and exotic things, but I love my family and home.  I also love art and have worked closely with the museums and galleries in our area.
My husband David, also present, is a professional studio musician and performer/singer/songwriter who has a recording studio in our home. He also loves skiing, art, and great books.

name: Architectural Masterpiece with Roof Deck
host_about:
I love meeting new people and welcoming them to Venice. My house  has been a labor of love and a reflection of my passion for music , art and celebrating life.

 I enjoy walking on the  beach as well as to nearby Abbott Kinney street, named by GQ magazine as "The coolest block in America". I am confident will enjoy the trendsetting shops, art galleries and world class restaurants and bars as much as I do!  

As owner and creative director of Santa Barbara Design studio, I love design and shopping,  If you are a creative professional, I would be happy to point you in the direction of must see shopping areas, clubs,  and the coolest shops while you are in L.A.

name: Los Angeles Area Rancho Equestrian.
host_about:
I am a horse lover and spend as much of my time with them as possible. We breed the rare Andalusian breed originally from Spain (the horse on which most "Knight" chess pieces are modeled. Our horses are movie stars, have been featured in books and magazines and are all around worldly and wise. I love to travel, been to various islands, Poland, Hungry, Austria and England. Can't wait to see more of our beautiful planet. I am a music buff and appreciate all genres of music. My husband and I are both passionate, fun-loving people.  

I'm Randy, the "horse-husband," skilled at mucking stalls and changing water buckets. In my spare time from that, I'm an attorney and a mortgage lending company owner.  I'm also an owner of a fledgling film production company.  Like Phyllis, I'm an avid reader, hence our large library, though my taste runs to classics and to baseball.  I've been an adult league hardball baseball player for the past 19 years (left field).  We both have a lot of other interests and enjoy good conversation over a glass of wine or cup of coffee.

name: Lets play in the sand!!!
host_about:
••• Welcome to Long Beach the International City!!!•••
 My background is Hungarian and I am originally from Europe. I love learning about other Cultures and this was the main reason I started doing ARBNB! 

Along the way I have met some truly wonderful people and am very fortunate. Of course there are always a couple of people that personalities clash with, but for the most part I am truly blessed.

 I love photography and animals.
Also enjoy to Cook!!!

If you need to be shown around the City and need a Tour guide I would be very happy to do so.
 
Please make sure to bring some slippers my house is shoe- or if you let me know your size I do have some extra ones.

Also I do have my lovely Luna my precious Cat and my little titty-baby Soli my Maltipoo that reside here.
My dog does go with his dad at times so he isn't here full time.

Thank you and please email me with any other questions.

name: Private Room In Hawthorne Near LAX
host_about:
I really enjoy hosting people.  I like to get to know my guests, and am willing to give them a local's prospective on things or show them around myself if I have time.  I took a trip to South America in January 2013 and really loved the Inca Trail and Colombia.  I went to Ireland and the UK in July 2013 and had a great time visiting with friends I met while traveling.  I've traveled to Europe and Asia. One of my favorite places was Almaty Kazakhstan. I'm heading to India this summer and am excited to explore New Delhi.

Some of my interests:

name: Suite near Universal
host_about:
I have enjoyed becoming a veteran host on Airbnb, having hosted over 2000 guests in my home since 2013, many of them returning again and again. I have learned so many new things from my guests that have made my life richer: things about their hometown, recipes, new websites, things I would never have learned otherwise. I feel really blessed that some of the most terrific people in the world have chosen my home to stay in and to share their wisdom with me. 
I am of Indian descent; my parents immigrated to the US from South India, and I have lived in Los Angeles since I was 2-years-old.  My hobby is collecting "old" technology. I find it fascinating how quickly technology is changing.  I have a 1950 television, an antique record player, a camera, a telegraph machine, and a telephone in my collection. My favorite food is dark chocolate-- I have to have a bite a day! I love being a tourist in my own city, exploring all the special spots that most residents take for granted and never visit. I like learning the history behind a location, finding the best restaurants, and good movies and television!  When I visit a new city, it is important to me to stay in a spotless, ultra-comfortable place.  I love little luxuries, the best pancakes, the nicest sheets, the most comfortable pillow, the perfect cup of tea.  Things that irritate me when I travel are: getting lost and people that ruin my day with their not-friendly attitudes. Little details do matter, and I love making that difference for my guests.  I have worked as a tour guide, so I can give you those helpful hints that can make a huge difference when you are traveling.

name: Venice Original Private Guest House
host_about:
Hey Airbnb-ers

Nice too meet you, my name is Patrick Lennon and I was born and raised in Venice Beach, CA, part of one of the largest families in L.A., the Lennons.  Our family has been populating Venice since 1904, so you won't find a more local family.  I own and operate three companies, D2 Models, a nationwide modeling agency Klothwork, a distributor and retailer for sweatshirts and t-shirts and finally Book My Lot, an online resource for locating and booking food trucks around the country.  I ended up buying the house I grew up in located right in the heart of Venice to help take care of my mother and now live here with my beautiful wife Cristina.   We've decided to share it with world travelers and allow them to experience a big piece of Venice locality from location, to family, to food and entertainment.  We're extremely family oriented and have hundreds of friends and family around the neighborhood.  We love being social, just kickin' it on the couch with a good home cooked meal,  the company of others, travelling and meeting new people!  I worked in the restaurant industry before starting my companies so I have a great sense of what to see and what to do when in Venice for entertainment.  I work from home, am always here to help and because I am my own boss, I have the freedom to jump on a bike with my guests and show them around town.   We promise you'll love the stay and would much rather it be affordable and fun then expensive and boring!

Pasadena is noted for the largest parade in the world, Rose Parade that is coming up Jan. 1st. It ends a few blocks from our house. Then the Rose Bowl begins. The Phantom jets fly over the pool as the game begins. There a lot of history here, old  architecture, and waterfalls and canyons like Eaton Canyon 2 blocks from the house. I like to hike in this area and visit the overlooks with views from Pasadena to the Pacific Ocean. The weather is almost always great for outdoor activities and photography. It is so quiet here you can become very close to nature, as close as the back yard. I love going to the international restaurants, coffee shops, shopping, museums, gardens, and Santa Anita Race Track for endless fun in our quiet and cultured community.

She knows the South Bay, Long Beach, San Pedro and greater Los Angeles like the back of her hand -- so if you want the best Thai in Hollywood, kimchi in K-town,  taco truck in Boyle Heights,  Ethiopian or Jewish Deli on Fairfax-- she can direct you!

name: Bright New Beachside Master Suite
host_about:
My name is Elise and my friend, Sterling (a lifetime entrepreneur, eternal volunteer, animal advocate and now a commercial actor and model), and I would love to have you as our guest! 

I’m a former professional model that lived around the globe, and Sterling traveled around the world for entertainment and business, and you will love how those experiences translate into a better lodging experience for you. 

You are going to be very pleased with your stay in Santa Monica, because we have had hundreds of happy guests since joining Air BnB in March 2014 (under our previous partnership -- we’ve struck out on our own), and we always go the extra mile to satisfy your needs.

We have chosen to specialize within the bed and breakfast industry by offering only experiences of exceptional quality. Our objective is to be recognized as the leader that manages the finest bed and breakfasts in Santa Monica or wherever we locate. We are your home away from home, and we create lodgings of enduring value using warm design and finishes evocative of Classic Golden Era Hollywood, and support them with a deeply instilled ethic of personal service. Doing so allows us to satisfy the needs and tastes of our discriminating guests, and to maintain our position as a leading Santa Monica bed and breakfast host.

You are going to be delighted with the short walking distances to everything—the beach, 3rd Street Promenade, Santa Monica Pier, Palisades Park and Montana Avenue shops—and the beautiful scenery and the relaxing warm, very clean and friendly environment to come home to each night. Whether it’s bedside snacks and aromatic candles, fresh towels and high thread count sheets,  fully stocked bathrooms (cotton balls to Q-Tips, shampoo, shaving cream, toothpaste, mouthwash, deodorants, and more), a fully stocked kitchen, or thoroughly cleaned and spotless bathrooms and showers, we are confident that you are going to love staying at your home away from home.

When coming to Santa Monica Beach and the Los Angeles/Hollywood area, get the most from your travel budget with our clean, wonderfully appointed, beautifully decorated lodgings while saving money for dining, shopping, theme parks and California experiences. Welcome home!

Being a Claremont native, business owner, and 5C graduate, I think Claremont lacks comfortable hotels, and offering a space to host guest wanting to be in Claremont is important! It’s more convenient for guests and it allows people to support the small businesses in town versus outside the area! Due to Covid, I admittedly spend less time in person with guests, but I am always available by text for recommendations or troubleshooting. My boyfriend, Jake, is the co-host. name: Artist's Cabin, Clean, Quiet, WiFi, Parks &Trails.
host_about:
I am a 30 year veteran of the Adventure Sports/Commercial Television and Film World.  I grew up between the Mountains of Colorado, in Vail and Aspen, and a large cattle ranch in Northwest Montana.  After a year of school at Prescott College in Arizona and several more shooting ski films in Colorado, I moved to North Hollywood where I lasted about 6 months before fleeing to Half Moon Bay.  I eventually made it back to Hollywood because of "The Business" and for about 5 years lived on my sailboat.  Throughout this time I was traveling the world shooting films and first kayak descents of rivers and ski descents of mountains.  About 10 years ago I met my sweetheart at the Premier of an IMAX Film called "Mystery of the Nile" we shot while making the first "Source to Sea" descent of the Nile.  After a couple of years living in the Marina we decided to settle in Topanga with our young family.  As luck would have it, we found a magical piece of property, with direct access to over 100 miles of hiking/mountain biking trails through Topanga State Park and adjacent wild areas, while being only 22 miles direct from downtown Los Angeles.  Now I am able to work closer to home and family.  Airbnb along with some beautiful property with stunning views is helping fulfill that dream....
As far as hosting, I would personally like to make everyone who stays with us a lifelong friend but I am also just happy to share a such a beautiful place so close to the city, yet so far away from all the noise and haste!  
If you decide to stay with us, you are welcome to request additional services like breakfast, cappuccino or a shuttle to the airport, direction and information on local resources.  We will do what we can to make sure our guests have a wonderful stay in a truly magical place with no worries about the small stuff.

name: Briar Patch Rose Cottage
host_about:
Being a host and sharing my home with travelers from all around the world has added joy and fulfillment to my life. In addition to hosting,
I have a wonderful and rewarding job being an elementary school librarian. I enjoy being a musician and I play many musical instruments. Decorating my 1943 house with vintage items in shabby chic and romantic cottage style is my passion, it is truly a Rose Cottage. As a homeowner for twenty three years, I have learned how to fix "this old house" on a small budget, so being creative and resourceful are just part of daily life. The many local thrift stores and the occasional garage sales serve as outlets for relaxing and meeting new people. 
I am a fan of Star Wars and enjoy collecting their merchandise. Everyday I update my boards on Pinterest where I share pictures of my house and share my passions. I have over 12,000 followers on Pinterest. It is my dream someday to be a published author of children's books and have a specialty used book store. My life motto is to be the kind of person that I would want in my life.

Hi!  We are the Harrisons and we look forward to meeting you!  

We are early to bed and early to rise (5am every morning.)
Michael spends the majority of his time remodeling and doing handyman work. He is also an actor, so he has the occasional self-tape or online audition to take care of in the living room.  Jennifer is a dancer and fitness instructor. While Michael is mostly gone during the day, sometimes you’ll have to share the living space with Jennifer while she teaches her online barre classes. 
We all share the space with our amazing dogs, Ajax and Bullet. Ajax is a sweet, sleepy Lab mix and Bullet is our feisty Basset Hound. Neither bite, both are friendly, and you’ll hear more from Bullet than Ajax, considering he is still a puppy. 

We love playing volleyball on the beach and are always looking for an adventure on the weekends.
We so look forward to hosting you! 

Do everything you can to do everything you can!

name: 2-BR Canyon Getaway Sleeps 5-6
host_about:
Hi I’m Mary!

I love meeting people from around the world. Our travels have taken us all over America and to more than 20 countries around the globe.  In the late 90’s we lived for about two years in the Dominican Republic.  I have also loved being home, raising my kids, giving parties and opening our California home to friends who have stayed for months on their way to the next stop in their life journey.    AirBnB Hosting offers us an opportunity to bring our passion for meeting people from around the globe and our passion for hospitality together.  We hope we can help make your visit to California a great experience.

I have been an educator in the La Crescenta area for the last 16 years of my life, working with children in the public schools and at my church. Before that I was a television producer in Cleveland, Ohio.  My husband Andy is the busy pastor of a local La Crescenta  church. Part of his ministry includes leading mission teams to the Dominican Republic, Mexico and the Sierras. He speaks Spanish, and I am always learning. My daughter Holly is in and out of town; she often helps us with hosting while she's home in the summer. We are looking forward to our AirBnB adventure with you!

name: Cozy room with one queen bed（舒适的房间，房东中国人）
host_about: My wife is Chinese and I am American.  We live in the beautiful city of Alhambra, California. Alhambra is a satellite city that makes up the greater Los Angeles area. We are 7 miles from downtown Los Angeles and 4 blocks away from the I-10 freeway. Every service that you might need is within a one mile radius of our home (supermarkets, fast food, drugstore, dentist, doctor and hospital). Our apartment includes one living room and two bedrooms. The guest room has one queen-size bed. We also have a bunk bed that is located next to the living room with no separating wall. It is a curtained-off area without doors. In all reality, we could be of service to 2 people comfortably and 3 with a little more effort. We would (and you), would find it very difficult to sleep 4 people because of privacy and bathroom needs. We all have to share 1 bathroom in this apartment. Parking requires a city permit sticker, but we do have a small garage in the rear that would not cost you. I lived and worked in China for 6 years as an English teacher and professional conductor of the Changsha Wind Symphony. I am sure we could all exchange some interesting cultural conversations. We have welcomed guests from France, Korea, Chile, Spain, China and obviously, America.  Our home will be spoken Chinese and English. We have always welcomed guests from around the world and never once had a problem. We have wi-fi, TV, icebox, stove, etc. for your use. Sorry, no pets allowed (management). If you smoke just step outside.  No problem-- I am a smoker. Allow us to be your host and make our home, your home, for the duration of your stay.  If you are looking for a place to stay for a while, this is perfect. Check-out time by 11:00 a.m. the day of departure. Check-in time from 3:00 p.m. until no later than 11:00 p.m. unless special arrangements are made.

name: Casa Dino Hollywood Hills Guest Suite & Patio
host_about:
I get great pleasure from meeting new people and in sharing my beautiful home with you. I have just finished remodeling and updating this special little guest unit and private patio and I have done so with a visiting guest in mind - just like you. It is my goal to provide you with lasting memories of your time here in Los Angeles and I will do anything I can to help you achieve just that -  right down to the last little detail, namely:  for those cold mornings there is the towel warmer in your bathroom, for your listening pleasure the Bose Soundlink Mini II bluetooth sound system, for atmosphere we have installed  LED lighting strips carefully positioned throughout,  for your reading pleasure we offer a small yet distinct  collection of great reads all with the great City of Los Angeles showcased as the backdrop to their individual storylines.  In that library you have access to information on interesting things to do and places to see while in our great city, and for your viewing pleasure a brand new 32" Roku/ SMART TV,  you also will find personalized "Casa Dino" stationary. envelopes  and postcards along with complimentary office supplies in your pop down desk/ computer work station, for your security  there is a private laptop safe, we also have a special wall featuring Los Angeles "themed" maps of the City and various neighborhoods and to top it all off you will enjoy your complimentary morning coffee experience featuring the Keurig MINI plus Brewing System and an assortment of  K-pods to suit your individual tastes. 
     I have resided in Los Angeles my entire life, so I am a terrific resource when it comes to the history of our City, the layout of the many neighborhoods, off the beaten path things to see or do or even the hottest new restaurant, drinking spot, romantic night out or dance club. You may even prefer to stay in and prepare a meal for yourself in your own newly remodeled private and fully equipped kitchen. Or perhaps take in some sun and read a great book on your own private patio or take a cool dip poolside. It's all good...Being situated in the Hollywood Hills, don't be surprised as you take a stroll, jog or bike  through the neighborhood to spot well-known celebrities across the board from the world's of dance, stage, motion pictures or music industries. After all, this is one of the key areas where they choose to call home. 
     I love cooking and entertaining and I also have a passion for building. I have painstakingly completed most of the renovations to this original 1920's Mediterranean Villa myself and I am so very excited to share it with you.   I have also been in the restaurant and hospitality industry for most of my career, which is why hosting guests such as yourself is such a natural for me.
     So, without further delay,  I say to you..."mi casa, es tu casa,"  Yes, "my place is your place." Make that reservation now. I look forward to meeting and hosting you here at  "Casa Dino'" an Airbnb 5-Star property!"

host_about:
Hello...
Thank you for taking the time to look at our cozy home, "Casita Amoroso."  My name is Barbara, and I am 3rd generation, born and raised in Venice Beach, California.  I love my family and the beach!  I grew up just around the block in a family of 13 , with lots of cousins nearby ( ...most of us are still living, working, and playing in the Venice area!).  This is the first home my husband and I bought 49 years ago in the month we married.  Since then, it has been home to many many family members, including my daughter (your co-host), Katy, who currently resides in the cozy attached back unit with her college-aged son. Katy is a well-known local birth and postpartum doula who clearly loves babies, her family, and sprinkling her personal touches throughout the property. She prides herself in keeping everything clean and organized! 
This house holds such a special place in our hearts and we are so happy to be able to share it with you.  We've enjoyed renovating this 97-year old gem - bringing new life to the old charm.  We hope to make your stay in Venice a memorable one, and we look forward to meeting you!

name: Stay in LA LA Land at The Blue Moon Bungalow
host_about:
Hello there! Thank you for visiting our listings for CASA LUNA and BLUE MOON BUNGALOW.

 CASA LUNA features architecture & design elements of all the places we've lived & loved. The Collection of folk art prevalent in its decor is a reflection of our restored 1920's Spanish home In Altadena.

BLUE MOON BUNGALOW is a 1 BR/ 1 Bath 600 sq ft sexy, cool, ultra modern guesthouse that pays homage to Hollywood in it's decor.

Being awarded SUPERHOST each quarter is the best reward and a great incentive to continue exceeding our guests expectations to provide them with a memorable time in our home. 

Kittie was born and bred sassy and smart in the south, energized and enlightened in the Land of Enchantment, rejuvenated and revitalized in Mexico, & self-actualized and sustained in California...
The words Wanderlust & adventuresome could be used to describe her. Her entrepreneurial & creative talents have been used in careers from owning an iconic retail shop in Santa Fe to owning a production company with her son, Whiskey Pete, a well-known vocalist, performer, & composer in Electronic Dance Music. 
Kittie underwent a life -changing cervical fusion surgery in 2013 & was given an opportunity for more life and more love. Her new life chapter began when this airbnb business was born following her long recovery. 

I am so blessed with an amazing life. I've been given children, family and friends that fill me with great contentment. My joy of life is a reflection of all that I  am grateful for and all the lessons I've learned along the way.

Airbnb has afforded me wonderful opportunities to meet people from all over the world and I love it. Who will cross our threshold today?
Kittie Brown

As a guest of the Broadlind Hotel, you will get a taste of staying in a historical building with great restaurants and entertainment all in one building.  We always strive to make your stay at the Hotel as comfortable and memorable as possible.

name: Stylish, Cozy oasis. Mid-City. Walk to metro!
host_about:
Hi,
Carlos and I have lived in LA for the last 6 years and we just renovated the guest house this year.
Carlos is a Swiss/Spanish actor & singer and I am Irish/Belgian acting coach and director. We have 2 kids, Elvis and Tyger.
Apart from our kids we love art, watching it and creating it;-) We enjoy adventures when we travel, and love not making any plans about it so we can discover and be surprised day by day.
Before LA we lived in Madrid, Paris and Switzerland and Belgium. Needless to say we love meeting travelers and we speak several languages so feel free to connect!

Carlos loves decoration so he has put a lot of good vibes and personal touches in our guest house so you can really relax and feel at home;-)

host_about:
Hello! Attorney by day, vintage motorcycle and car enthusiast by weekend :) I love exploring new places, trying to keep plants alive (and failing at it), and have an obsession with spicy food. 

I am a pretty easy going airbnb host - very hands off, but available if you need me. I hope you enjoy my home and exploring Long Beach.  xx.

name: A cozy designed Home in Diamond Bar near Disney
host_about: Hi, my name is JoJo, I come from China.  I graduated hotel management in Malaysia. Then I decided to go to LA to study again after I have my daughter. I thoroughly love this city where I am currently living. I like to travel around the world when I have a break and get a different experience from different hosts which I can improve my apartments. My goal is to provide you excellent customer service and make your stay as delightful as possible though.  I am here to help you have a unique experience and want you to come back! If you need check in earlier or late checkout, just let me know, and I will try my best to accommodate you. I have different style's apartments for you to choose, I believe that there is one you will like.

name: One or Optional Two Rooms in Enchanting Garden Cottage
host_about: I'm a designer/illustrator, classical pianist, and a master gardener, nuts about music, architecture & design. Easy-going and considerate, and appreciate the same. I just moved back to my beloved natal state after 30 years in the east. I've traveled extensively, and stayed at the finest hotels - so making your stay distinctively pleasant is important to me. It's been a lot of hard work to make my place serene, cosseting and beautiful, and I'd love to share it with you. I speak French like a Spanish cow, Spanish like a French cow, and Japanese like an eggplant.

name: The Urban | Big NY Style Loft Pershing Sq Views
host_about:
Hi, I am the Founder of Heather's Angels. Since 2015 we have helped over 250 hosts launch & run their Airbnb businesses. We believe that traveling reminds us that we are more alike, than different & everyone belongs.

Whatever brings you to town - our guests rave about "The Angels" fast responses as you are planning your trip. We provide you a neighborhood & city guide to help you make the most of your time with us,  live assistance from people that actually know the home, attention to detail, 5 star cleanliness guarantees for each stay (if you aren't happy with any part of the clean we will come back & redo, no questions, no charge), seamless check-in / out. 

Welcome, make yourself at home XOXO Heather's Angels

name: Colorful unique Train Caboose Cornell near malibu
host_about: I am a chef, author, restaurateur and philanthropist, and I arrived in Los Angeles from Northern Ireland in 1975, to begin my career in the culinary industry.  My  culinary expertise encompasses an international diversity including Indian, Chinese, Mexican, Japanese, French and, of course, Contemporary California and Irish. I have been featured in the L.A. Times, Fine Cooking Magazine, and Bon Appetit Magazine named (Website hidden by Airbnb) of the top six chefs in the United States”. Today, I own two  distinctively different restaurants on Main Street in Santa Monica,California: Lula Cocina Mexicana, a bold, bright and colorful cantina famous for its murals painted by artist Eloy Torrez, and Signature Lula Margaritas;and Finn McCool's Irish Pub, boasting a beautiful bar shipped painstakingly over from Ireland through the Panama Canal.In 1995, I  built my dream home, Rancho Chiquita, nestled high in the Malibu Mountains.  Rancho Chiquita overlooks a spectacular panoramic ocean view and 250 acres of rolling hills, and is host to many Charity Fundraising Events, Weddings , Private Cooking Classes , and Film and Movie Shoots. I am an avid advocate on behalf of the protection and rehabilitation of animals, and I share my home with a multitude of Rescue Dogs.

name: Daisy Place-Private Entrance, Kitchen, & Suite
host_about:
A traveler at heart! Before sharing this space with other fellow travelers, I have been to New Zealand, Australia, Maldives, Thailand, Japan, China, United Kingdom, Peru, and Mexico. I spent four months studying abroad in Japan before graduating from UCR (University of California, Riverside). In my free time, you will find me doing various kinds of sports, such as hiking, camping, cycling, scuba diving, and hang gliding.

Having traveled to a number of countries, I got a decent sense of the essential needs for travelers. My goal is to provide you a comfortable space with essential amenities, while saving from the extravagant services that you may not necessary need, so you’re left with more funds for traveling! If you need any recommendations on where to visit or eat in Los Angeles, please don’t be shy and let me know :).

name: Private & ISOLATED 3BR Hollywood Hills view home!
host_about:
AirBnb and renting a vacation rental doesn't need to be the unprofessional experience which some may have had in the past. All of our guests will experience a professional operation and I treat every guest and property as if it is a 5 star hotel experience. Professional cleaning crews, quality amenities, 24 hour contact information for myself and team to take care of any needs. In addition I will lend the personal knowledge that I have of Los Angeles to make sure everyone's experience is tailored to their wants and needs. 

I have been traveling and hosting using AirBnb for over 10 years now and consider myself a global citizen of world. With over 30 countries visited and staying in some of the best places (and worst), I strive to make peoples experiences as good as I can when visiting my home city of Los Angeles.

My goal is to make every fellow traveler feel at home in the City of Angels. All of our properties are met with the highest standards of cleanliness, decor, linens, FULLY stocked kitchens for cooking, and basic amenities such as spa quality shampoos and soaps.

I look forward to having you!

Follow us on IG also /laluxurybnb

name: Boho Chic residence
host_about:
One of the Westside’s top-tier brokers, Alicia Drake has a stellar reputation for performing at the very highest levels of real estate. Working with a distinguished local and international clientele, Alicia specializes in exceptional residential and commercial properties.  Powered by a background in interior design and architecture, her skillful negotiations, strategic counsel and insightful analysis have created hundreds of successful outcomes for buyers and sellers alike.

 

Alicia has been a premier agent since 2003 and with each transaction, she is true to her mission of creating lifelong relationships by offering the best experience possible, resulting in a large amount of repeat and referral business.. 

 

Innovative, experienced and creative, Alicia’s real estate acumen can fulfill the most sophisticated and ambitious property aspirations, as well as unique and challenging situations, with discretion, determination and success.  She is committed to delivering the highest level of ethics, integrity, personal service, professional representation and technical expertise, ensuring that every client is thrilled with the outcome and comfortable with the entire process.

 

“I’m committed to providing the ultimate level of real estate guidance from beginning to end. Through an honest and transparent work ethic, I passionately strive to find the ultimate success in real estate, be it in sale, purchase or investment opportunities,” she says. With a strong negotiating skill set, creative marketing background and architectural/interior design prowess, she offers a high level of competence that can bring opportunity and profitability to each transaction. With her focused, grounded and professional attitude, every turn of the buying or selling process is guided seamlessly and with clear intent, allowing her clients to enjoy a positive experience throughout.

 

A graduate of the Ecole de Beaux Arts in Paris France, Alicia studied art and design at the Ecole du Louvre.  She is active in the community, supporting a variety of causes that better the lives of local residents.

name: Admire Amazing Views from a Modern, Zen-like Guest Suite
host_about:
My husband Tino and I  - Pia - moved to LA from Berlin in 2008. Tino is a designer in the entertainment industry while I work as an artist. We have a five year old son named Yoko who is fun and very happy little monkey. He was the reason why we eventually left our loft in the arts district behind to build and design  our custom dream home in the hills of echo park. The house has three levels and we live in the two top floors above the air bnb unit. Tino and I have lived in five different countries and have always been passionate about traveling. Our favorite places where we recently spent our vacations at are Tulum and pretty much all over Italy... We love to cook and share food with friends. Tino loves collecting books and vinyl and of course we love watching movies. Lately we have been hooked on the italian directors of I am love/ A Bigger splash (Luca Guadagnino) and The Great Beauty/ Consequences of Love (Paolo Sorrentino)….Yoko loves his Pixar movies such as ‘Coco’ or ’Toy Story’. Meeting new people, exploring new cultures and enjoying life has always been super important and a driving energy for us. We love living in LA...foremost the weather but we also appreciate the chilled vibe of the city. It makes us happy to make others feel comfortable and enjoy our LA home and the city as much as we do! 


Here is a link that gives some insight in the design process of the house for those who are interested.

Hello guests, 
We are your hosts from nMatter partners, Since the time we have started hosting on Airbnb, its been a wonderful journey, met some wonderful people. We love meeting  people but always give guests the privacy they want.  we want our guests to  enjoy a quality home away from home experience. Guests feedback and reviews are very important as they help me understand their expectations and experiences during their stay. 

Important Note to our guests:  

1. For best experience at our place, please do not wait until your check out to let us know you had some issue. we try our best to be attentive hosts and be available to address any questions/concerns/issues during your stay.

2. We DO NOT have camera's inside of our units, the security camera's are outside (parking lot, yard, patio etc). we totally understand guests concern as we hear so many horrible stories out there. Rest assured guests privacy is our top priority, we do not compromise on that. PLEASE let me know ASAP if you have any concerns, we will address them Immediately.

Thank you to every guest who stayed with us, we look forward to host you.

I am fluent in English, I lived in Germany for years so I can speak and understand it, though my reading and writing isn't very good. I can also speak and understand Mandarin Chinese, sadly I cannot read or write in Chinese. host_about:
Hi, we are Chris, Jen, Toddler Emerson & Baby Madison!

I am a private chef from the East Coast/Italy and my wife is a local/Brit in human rights work!

We have converted our multi-generational Malibu family property into an absolutely stunning Airbnb oasis that is private, stylish, and close to the best beaches, as well as town hot spots (the only shared space is the parking entrance to ensure your upmost privacy is taken care of).

Here you will find a vineyard, orchard, pond, infinity pool, macrame swings, stew grill, hammock, outdoor dining, gazebos, hot tub, Wifi, vintage soaking tub with rain shower, stone walkin shower, smart TVs, fireplaces, high speed wifi, kids toys, central location, celebrity hot spot lookout, easy Uber/DoorDash, private parking, full hotel organic bath+kitchen amenities, secret access to famous state park, beach club additions/clearance, room service, mini-bar, lots of lawn games, firepit tables, tee pee, kayak/paddle-boards, organic vegetable garden & lots more to enjoy! 

We are so happy to open our Malibu oasis for you to enjoy, so anything else we can do to ensure it’s a great stay, just let us know!

Cheers!!!

name: Clean, Quiet, Tipi w/WiFi, in Wilderness Near LA 2
host_about:
I am a 30 year veteran of the Adventure Sports/Commercial Television and Film World.  I grew up between the Mountains of Colorado, in Vail and Aspen, and a large cattle ranch in Northwest Montana.  After a year of school at Prescott College in Arizona and several more shooting ski films in Colorado, I moved to North Hollywood where I lasted about 6 months before fleeing to Half Moon Bay.  I eventually made it back to Hollywood because of "The Business" and for about 5 years lived on my sailboat.  Throughout this time I was traveling the world shooting films and first kayak descents of rivers and ski descents of mountains.  About 10 years ago I met my sweetheart at the Premier of an IMAX Film called "Mystery of the Nile" we shot while making the first "Source to Sea" descent of the Nile.  After a couple of years living in the Marina we decided to settle in Topanga with our young family.  As luck would have it, we found a magical piece of property, with direct access to over 100 miles of hiking/mountain biking trails through Topanga State Park and adjacent wild areas, while being only 22 miles direct from downtown Los Angeles.  Now I am able to work closer to home and family.  Airbnb along with some beautiful property with stunning views is helping fulfill that dream....
As far as hosting, I would personally like to make everyone who stays with us a lifelong friend but I am also just happy to share a such a beautiful place so close to the city, yet so far away from all the noise and haste!  
If you decide to stay with us, you are welcome to request additional services like breakfast, cappuccino or a shuttle to the airport, direction and information on local resources.  We will do what we can to make sure our guests have a wonderful stay in a truly magical place with no worries about the small stuff.

name: Burbank hill, pvt room ideal for LA/studio work
host_about:
Hi. Thank you for taking an interest in me and viewing my home. The house was built in 1944 , and we  take pride in maintaining  the history of the home, while expanding and upgrading it over the last 26 years. My 2 boys have grown up here, and done very well. My oldest son is majoring in computer science at the University of Colorado in Colorado Springs. My younger son is on his way to accepting many offers  from several universities. So I guess I am what you call  and an "empty nester". I love  having  people in my home and feel very  lucky to have had wonderful  guests, and I look forward to having more.  It's been an honor to meet people  I would never otherwise have met, had it not been for Airbnb.

 Burbank is a wonderful community that is very safe and friendly. My home is very close to  several motion picture studios  as well as the Burbank Airport, so it is especially convenient for those in the motion picture studio business and related industries. There are also many resources for those  looking for additional business accommodations, such as conference  rooms, event halls and training facilities. I am so fortunate to live in a location  that is also close to  many attractions,  including  theme parks, hiking and biking trails, fantastic  restaurants and great live music. As a longtime Burbank resident, I can say it is  a world  renowned city with a small-town atmosphere. Many of the residents  are 3rd generation and  continue  to stay because of the friendships and wonderful community support. So I can definitely recommend the best the area has to offer!

 I have an art studio in my detached garage where I work, so I am close by but not intrusive if guests would like privacy. I enjoy entertaining and providing  extras for my  guests.  I hope you consider my home  for your stay while you travel.

name: Hollywood Hills ~ Le Paradis
host_about: I have lived in this home since I was a child and have found it to be a very peaceful & healing place over these many years. It was built in 1922 making it almost 100 years old! It has a fascinating history, undeniable charm character and energy and has always been filled with love and laughter. I am so happy to be able to now share it with others as a host. I love laughter  music, animals, art and the sound of rain (to name just a few). I enjoy quiet afternoons working in the garden & fireside chats with old friends. I believe in helping others and always showing kindness. I enjoy photography as a hobby, and watching foreign films. Life can be pretty hectic and complicated at times, so my main goal on any given day is to try and find perspective and remember to smile!

I’m a classically trained chef and have worked a little in the industry.  But because I have many interests, I didn’t want to give up the balance. So, to make things more manageable, I use my culinary skills to make donuts for my guests whenever possible. 

What to expect from our listing and being our guest...  We have only the one listing. Our guesthouse is an extension of our home. We treat every guest as if they are family visiting.  It’s been designed for comfort, privacy and is packed with amenities.

We welcome anyone who would be respectful of our home, to enjoy the space equally as much as we do.  And we hope you come back again. 

God bless you.

name: Charming, Convenient, Spacious and Private Place
host_about:
Hello guests, 
We are your hosts from nMatter partners, Since the time we have started hosting on Airbnb, its been a wonderful journey, met some wonderful people. We love meeting  people but always give guests the privacy they want.  we want our guests to  enjoy a quality home away from home experience. Guests feedback and reviews are very important as they help me understand their expectations and experiences during their stay. 

Important Note to our guests:  

1. For best experience at our place, please do not wait until your check out to let us know you had some issue. we try our best to be attentive hosts and be available to address any questions/concerns/issues during your stay.

2. We DO NOT have camera's inside of our units, the security camera's are outside (parking lot, yard, patio etc). we totally understand guests concern as we hear so many horrible stories out there. Rest assured guests privacy is our top priority, we do not compromise on that. PLEASE let me know ASAP if you have any concerns, we will address them Immediately.

Thank you to every guest who stayed with us, we look forward to host you.

I’m planning on working (ride-sharing at the moment is all I can do) a lot to build up my savings. WOuld love to stay In West Hollywood/ west LA area since I’ve lived here for years. I’ll be gone mostly working, going to doctors appointments, physical therapy and getting back in the gym. When I’m home I’m extremely neat and tidy (ex-Military), quiet, respectful,wouldn’t have guests, and VERY easy to get along with and most always have a positive attitude. Also, I love animals cooking and have a flexible schedule so I could help out with household duties if need be. Hope I sound like a good candidate and look forwArd to meeting you soon :) -Franco

name: Clean, Quiet,Tipi w/WiFi, in Wilderness Near LA
host_about:
I am a 30 year veteran of the Adventure Sports/Commercial Television and Film World.  I grew up between the Mountains of Colorado, in Vail and Aspen, and a large cattle ranch in Northwest Montana.  After a year of school at Prescott College in Arizona and several more shooting ski films in Colorado, I moved to North Hollywood where I lasted about 6 months before fleeing to Half Moon Bay.  I eventually made it back to Hollywood because of "The Business" and for about 5 years lived on my sailboat.  Throughout this time I was traveling the world shooting films and first kayak descents of rivers and ski descents of mountains.  About 10 years ago I met my sweetheart at the Premier of an IMAX Film called "Mystery of the Nile" we shot while making the first "Source to Sea" descent of the Nile.  After a couple of years living in the Marina we decided to settle in Topanga with our young family.  As luck would have it, we found a magical piece of property, with direct access to over 100 miles of hiking/mountain biking trails through Topanga State Park and adjacent wild areas, while being only 22 miles direct from downtown Los Angeles.  Now I am able to work closer to home and family.  Airbnb along with some beautiful property with stunning views is helping fulfill that dream....
As far as hosting, I would personally like to make everyone who stays with us a lifelong friend but I am also just happy to share a such a beautiful place so close to the city, yet so far away from all the noise and haste!  
If you decide to stay with us, you are welcome to request additional services like breakfast, cappuccino or a shuttle to the airport, direction and information on local resources.  We will do what we can to make sure our guests have a wonderful stay in a truly magical place with no worries about the small stuff.

host_about:
Hello there! I’m Lucy. I grew up in a town called Blackpool in northwest England. My desire for different experiences, travel and good weather drove me to move to Charleston, SC for college as a teenager. Since then, I’ve moved to NYC; Bangkok, Thailand; Vancouver, BC; and most recently, Los Angeles! 

My husband, Terence (or TJ), and I love AirBnB! We’ve stayed in some amazing Airbnb places throughout the world (our favorite was a little place up in the mountains in Ella, Sri Lanka) and loved our experience with the hosts so much that we decided to host here in LA! 

For fun, I enjoy making pottery, gardening, doing home improvements, hiking, being a puppy mama, and spending time with our friends. I’m most passionate about travel (seeing the non-touristy sides of places), culture, health and wellness.

name: Gorgeous Tiny House Agoura near Malibu 2bed/1bath
host_about: I am a chef, author, restaurateur and philanthropist, and I arrived in Los Angeles from Northern Ireland in 1975, to begin my career in the culinary industry.  My  culinary expertise encompasses an international diversity including Indian, Chinese, Mexican, Japanese, French and, of course, Contemporary California and Irish. I have been featured in the L.A. Times, Fine Cooking Magazine, and Bon Appetit Magazine named (Website hidden by Airbnb) of the top six chefs in the United States”. Today, I own two  distinctively different restaurants on Main Street in Santa Monica,California: Lula Cocina Mexicana, a bold, bright and colorful cantina famous for its murals painted by artist Eloy Torrez, and Signature Lula Margaritas;and Finn McCool's Irish Pub, boasting a beautiful bar shipped painstakingly over from Ireland through the Panama Canal.In 1995, I  built my dream home, Rancho Chiquita, nestled high in the Malibu Mountains.  Rancho Chiquita overlooks a spectacular panoramic ocean view and 250 acres of rolling hills, and is host to many Charity Fundraising Events, Weddings , Private Cooking Classes , and Film and Movie Shoots. I am an avid advocate on behalf of the protection and rehabilitation of animals, and I share my home with a multitude of Rescue Dogs.

name: Venice Beach 2 Blocks from Abbot Kinney Blvd.
host_about: I love travel, so naturally I love Airbnb. Some of my favorite international destinations have been Cuba, Nepal, Ireland (especially Donegal and "the North"), Istanbul, India, Pakistan, and London. I'm also a regular at the Sundance and Toronto film festivals. I lived in New York (Manhattan and Montauk) for decades, but then I fell in love with the mountains near Asheville NC, where I moved for 14 years. Now I'm living more happily than ever in Venice Beach, Los Angeles. I loved the Airbnb house I was renting in Venice so much that I bought it!  Now I'm an Airbnb host in Venice, like my landlord before me. I enjoy encountering so many nice and interesting guests, including film directors, journalists, producers, international visitors, and others from all walks of life. For work and even more excitement, I'm helping to run two film development, financing and production companies, Convergent Media and Divergent Pictures. I'm also a media and entertainment lawyer at the international law firm, SmithDehn LLP, which I co-founded. With locations in London, New York, Northern Ireland, India, Washington DC, Asheville, and LA, this "day job" suits my travel bug quite nicely!

Please take the time to go over the entire profile just one more time.

So please treat my place like your own and keep it clean.  The kitchen, the room, bathroom and living room.  The property has basic wear and tear but it's clean and maintained.  Again, it's not a motel/hotel  so if you are looking for immaculate and perfection, this wouldn't be a good fit.  Pe'Sha is simply somewhere to lay your head and do your thing while traveling.

name: Amenity-Rich Abbot Kinney Venice Oasis!
host_about: I love travel, so naturally I love Airbnb. Some of my favorite international destinations have been Cuba, Nepal, Ireland (especially Donegal and "the North"), Istanbul, India, Pakistan, and London. I'm also a regular at the Sundance and Toronto film festivals. I lived in New York (Manhattan and Montauk) for decades, but then I fell in love with the mountains near Asheville NC, where I moved for 14 years. Now I'm living more happily than ever in Venice Beach, Los Angeles. I loved the Airbnb house I was renting in Venice so much that I bought it!  Now I'm an Airbnb host in Venice, like my landlord before me. I enjoy encountering so many nice and interesting guests, including film directors, journalists, producers, international visitors, and others from all walks of life. For work and even more excitement, I'm helping to run two film development, financing and production companies, Convergent Media and Divergent Pictures. I'm also a media and entertainment lawyer at the international law firm, SmithDehn LLP, which I co-founded. With locations in London, New York, Northern Ireland, India, Washington DC, Asheville, and LA, this "day job" suits my travel bug quite nicely!

I keep HGTV on 24/7 when I'm not watching "The Walking Dead", "Billions", "Power", or the "Real Housewives"!  I love all types of music.  I grew up on the Motown sound, The Beatles, Elvis, Frank Sinatra & Johnny Mathis.  Currently, I love most rap music and most pop music.  I love Kendrick Lamar, Eminem, Lady Ga Ga, Pink!, Ed Sheeran, Bruno Mars, Adele, Maroon 5, Jay Z and Beyonce, to name a few.  I love my family.  Most of my brothers and sisters live nearby.  Some of my favorite restaurants are Javier's in Century City, The Little Kitchen of Italy in Westchester, Ruth Chris, Killer Shrimp, and of course the always reliable Cheesecake Factory in the Marina!  I guess my motto in life is. . .if you don't stand for something, you'll fall for anything.  I stand for human and equal rights.  Do unto others. . .and we'll all be alright!

name: Little Bali away from Home
host_about: Hi!    I live in the NoHo Arts District, in a cute little guest house.  I used to travel a lot for work and have the opportunity to offer my space for rent when I’m away, but now I have been staying in the main house (thanks, Covid) on the property instead, so I’m still able to rent out Little Bali.  My place is inspired by a trip I took to Indonesia- where ironically I stayed in an Air BnB with an amazing host who encouraged me to also host on the site if I ever had the opportunity- so here I am!  The space is a guest house that’s unattached to the main house, in a quiet and very safe neighborhood.  It’s totally enclosed within a backyard with high walls and a locking gate, with ample street parking. (The only restrictions are for street sweeping on Tuesdays and Wednesdays, but even then parking is easy).  There is a dog in the front house but hes so cute and friendly and would love to play with you-  if you don’t like dogs I can arrange for him to not be in the yard during your visit. I have a lot of knowledge to offer you about LA and what you should do while you’re here, so feel free to ask!

name: Hannah's Lovely Walnut Trail Villa
host_about:
I am Quiet,positive and easy-going. I Welcome people who have their own traveling stories and who have Much traveling experience. 
What is the hunger? The yelling? The incompletion that drives me to travel? 
Travel for the sound, the screak of winds and still air. Travel for the silence, silence beget reverence. Travel for the unknown, the unknownable . Travel for companionship. Travel for solitude. To touch the earth. To feel the earth surge...And remind ourselves what is!

name: Cozy bedroom in Central Rowland Heights! 羅蘭崗 雅緻單人房
host_about:
Hello, my name is Jenny, I am an Airbnb host most of the time and traveler only on occasion.

***Several of my family members, including myself, have asthma, so we have a strict NO SMOKING policy inside of our AirBnB listings, thank you for understanding.***

I'm quiet and tidy. As long as I have internet connection, I am happily entertained. I love animals, though I am allergic to most animal furs and dander (as well as most pollens). I'm a huge fan of Disney movies and enjoy action movies too. 

I am fluent in English, I lived in Germany for years so I can speak and understand it, though my reading and writing isn't very good. I can also speak and understand Mandarin Chinese, sadly I cannot read or write in Chinese. But fear not, any questions written in Chinese will be passed to my mother who will translate or reply for me. :)

I am working during the week days (and sometimes even the weekends) but I can and do reply to inquiries. It just might take a little while. Thank you for understanding!

name: Little Bali Guesthouse - A Peaceful Staycation
host_about: Hi!    I live in the NoHo Arts District, in a cute little guest house.  I used to travel a lot for work and have the opportunity to offer my space for rent when I’m away, but now I have been staying in the main house (thanks, Covid) on the property instead, so I’m still able to rent out Little Bali.  My place is inspired by a trip I took to Indonesia- where ironically I stayed in an Air BnB with an amazing host who encouraged me to also host on the site if I ever had the opportunity- so here I am!  The space is a guest house that’s unattached to the main house, in a quiet and very safe neighborhood.  It’s totally enclosed within a backyard with high walls and a locking gate, with ample street parking. (The only restrictions are for street sweeping on Tuesdays and Wednesdays, but even then parking is easy).  There is a dog in the front house but hes so cute and friendly and would love to play with you-  if you don’t like dogs I can arrange for him to not be in the yard during your visit. I have a lot of knowledge to offer you about LA and what you should do while you’re here, so feel free to ask!

name: Sofi / Rams Stadium 10min LAX aka"The Quiet Place"
host_about:
Pe'Sha is "The Place to Stay".  A relaxing place that's affordable, simple, cozy and very quiet.  

About Your Host:  Hi, I'm Miss very straightforward and direct, in case you can't tell by reading my listings lol.  I have a passion for business, learning new things and helping others.  I am single, no kids except for my Airbnb listings are my babies that's why I gave them names hahaha, and I take good care of them to share with you.  I choose to be HAPPY almost all the time.  I am very honest, ethical and trustworthy.

 I love a good conversation with my guest or just leaving you alone and let you do your thing, unless you are violating my rules then you have to leave. 

MUST READ:

Please take the time to go over the entire profile just one more time.

The Pe'Sha places are NOT Hotels,  I don't charge a cleaning because I wanted to limit my guest cost.  So if you choose to book with me it's mandatory that you clean up behind yourself.  So please treat my place like your own and keep it clean.  The kitchen, the room, bathroom and living room.  The property has basic wear and tear but it's clean and maintained.  Again, it's not a motel/hotel  so if you are looking for immaculate and perfection, this wouldn't be a good fit.  Pe'Sha is simply somewhere to lay your head and do your thing while traveling.

Hi, my name is Stuart and I'm a born and raised New Yorker living in Los Angeles with my family. Serial entrepreneur and owner of LA's most trusted and popular short-term rental company, Stay Awhile Villas.    I have traveled the world and love passing along my best travel experiences to our guests by making you feel like a member of an expensive travel club.   We have a beautiful collection of luxury residences including some of our own in the most popular neighborhoods in Los Angeles, Beverly Hills, Hollywood Hills, and of course Malibu.  We are extremely accomplished hosts on Airbnb with the following accolades:

According to AIRDNA in 2022 Stay Awhile Villas ranks #4 in the country and #1 in California!  California is the 2nd largest market in the US.

   -  21x's Airbnb Superhost
   -  17 LUX Listings
    - 1750+ 5-Star reviews

Our properties have been featured in Travel + Leisure, Angeleno, People Magazine, FOX, NBC, Wall Street Journal, Daily Mail, TMZ, History Channel, Mansion Global, Los Angeles Times, New York Times, and more.  Our guests include some of the most famous film and music personalities, C level executives of Fortune 500 companies, and Royal Families. 

Whether you are coming here for vacation, business, or pleasure we are here to make your stay as simple and luxurious as possible.  We offer the following services to our guests via our concierge partner(*additional fees may apply):

    - Personal Chefs and Catering
    - Vacation Planning and Excursion Recommendations 
    - Luxury Vehicle Rentals from Drive Awhile
    - Chauffeur Services from Drive Awhile
    - Yacht/Jet Charters 
   
See all our Airbnb portfolio of listings here: www.airbnb.com/p/los-angeles-vacation-rentals   I would also recommend you read our incredible reviews - https://www.airbnb.com/users/reviews/ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) Thank you for taking the time to read a little about us and we look forward to working with you. 

We have a diverse team fluent in multiple languages including English, Spanish, French, Italian and Serbo-Croatian/Bosnian.


Stuart Heller and the Stay Awhile Team

name: **MODERN & SUNNY 3BR FAMILY HOME W/ POOL/ BBQ**
host_about:
AirBnb and renting a vacation rental doesn't need to be the unprofessional experience which some may have had in the past. All of our guests will experience a professional operation and I treat every guest and property as if it is a 5 star hotel experience. Professional cleaning crews, quality amenities, 24 hour contact information for myself and team to take care of any needs. In addition I will lend the personal knowledge that I have of Los Angeles to make sure everyone's experience is tailored to their wants and needs. 

I have been traveling and hosting using AirBnb for over 10 years now and consider myself a global citizen of world. With over 30 countries visited and staying in some of the best places (and worst), I strive to make peoples experiences as good as I can when visiting my home city of Los Angeles.

My goal is to make every fellow traveler feel at home in the City of Angels. All of our properties are met with the highest standards of cleanliness, decor, linens, FULLY stocked kitchens for cooking, and basic amenities such as spa quality shampoos and soaps.

I look forward to having you!

Follow us on IG also /laluxurybnb

Peter and Amy

name: Luxury Spa-like Guesthouse
host_about: I am a Transaction Coordinator and Legal Assistant in the real estate and legal field.  I am a native of Los Angeles and have traveled extensively in Europe, Australia, Mexico and Canada.  I welcome international travelers!   I'm very laid back and friendly.  I love a big mug of strong coffee in the morning and a glass of cabernet in the evening.  I am a movie buff.  I have worked at various major motion picture studios for 17 years.  I keep HGTV on 24/7 when I'm not watching "The Walking Dead", "Billions", "Power", or the "Real Housewives"!  I love all types of music.  I grew up on the Motown sound, The Beatles, Elvis, Frank Sinatra & Johnny Mathis.  Currently, I love most rap music and most pop music.  I love Kendrick Lamar, Eminem, Lady Ga Ga, Pink!, Ed Sheeran, Bruno Mars, Adele, Maroon 5, Jay Z and Beyonce, to name a few.  I love my family.  Most of my brothers and sisters live nearby.  Some of my favorite restaurants are Javier's in Century City, The Little Kitchen of Italy in Westchester, Ruth Chris, Killer Shrimp, and of course the always reliable Cheesecake Factory in the Marina!  I guess my motto in life is. . .if you don't stand for something, you'll fall for anything.  I stand for human and equal rights.  Do unto others. . .and we'll all be alright!

name: Oaktree Studio & Micro Farm-Sanitized & SuperClean
host_about:
My husband, Javier, and I love to travel. Javier is from Madrid and I am a LA native.
 I have lived in Nepal and Thailand, each for a month, London for a year and Japan for almost 4 years working for the Japanese government as an English teacher.  Between us we speak English, French, Spanish and some Japanese. 

I have a BFA in fine art and I started my own business with the money I saved in Japan doing decorative painting in high-end homes: gold leaf, sky ceilings, limewash finishes, frescoes, egg tempera and other decorative finishes. I love to paint, design and draw.

Javier and I are also crazy about Japanese design and we are inspired by the culture, architecture and food. 
Maybe you will feel a Japanese sensibility when you visit?

host_about:
South Pasadena, CA is the filming location for the 1978 horror classic Halloween.

SugarMynt Gallery is the art gallery located behind the original Michael Myers house in South Pas. SugarMynt showcases BTS photos from the first two Halloween films, along side Hocus Pocus memorabilia, artworks and photos opps in their year round Haddonfield room. They host an annual highly anticipated Halloween exhibit, Welcome To Haddonfield, dedicated to the film, since they opened in 2015. Throughout the year, they host interchanging themed exhibits with a focus on where everyday is Halloween

name: Beach is Calling! Free Breakfast, Heated Pool, Beach, Near Hollywood Bowl
host_about:
Going someplace new is always exciting. And what would that adventure be without a great place to lay your head at the end of the day? That is where I come in!

As an avid traveler myself, I know how the little things can set the pace for a new experience! You want something hospitable and inviting to give you a remarkable experience that no one else can give you. A heated pool, or jacuzzi at the end of the day to relax in, or a nice meal within walking distance? Down to beds that cozy and homily. Sounds good? Well, you have come to the right place.

We offer handpicked accommodations in remarkable properties for a  top-notch experience with a few added extras. As well as tips, recommendations, and 24/7 customer support to make sure that your experience is the best it can be!

name: Beautiful & Clean home near Pasadena
host_about:
My husband Gerry and I owned travel agencies & Real Estate companies and are very tuned in to travelers and their intricate needs.  We go to Maui, Hawaii  and Waynesboro, PA at least 2 times per year to  update/freshen up our units.  Gerry is a licensed building contractor and he likes to update and work on properties;) And I like to decorate, stage properties, plant & design flower gardens.  

  For travelers coming to Los Angeles, we have 2 homes on Beachwood Dr. in Hollywood Hills that can accommodate from 1 to 14 people very central to Hollywood, Universal Studios and lots of tourist areas! Also a single unit that can accommodate 1 to 5 people in the Miracle Mile, very central to LAX Airport, Beverly Hills, Hollywood, Down Town Los Angeles, etc. And near Pasadena, CA  in Altadena, CA 

Plus 3 condos across from the Beach in Maui, Hawaii in S. Kiei near Wailea. 2 have direct ocean views.

 A 7,500sf Mansion in Waynesboro, PA  listed under “Beautiful Mansion in the Country”, which is also a Wedding Venue, we are licensed to host up to 32 people overnight and up to 120 for events.  Look us up when your travels call for these areas of the world. We look forward to hosting you and your family & friends.

    By the way, I also Speak Arabic and Amharic (Ethiopian language, which is not on the Airbnb language charts, I don't read or write Arabic, but speak it fluently).

    We love hosting people and making sure our guests are comfortable and happy:)

I was born and raised in Colombia and I've spent the last 20 years in California. I have worked in the financial industry for 24 years and currently, I work for a large bank. I love to travel, especially to Cartagena, where I spent a year as a teenager and where I recently bought a beautiful apartment, which I've listed on Airbnb. 

I love food, especially Colombian food. When I stay at my apartment in Cartagena I enjoy eating at my favorite restaurants near the apartment and I always find time to explore new eateries, which are plentiful in Cartagena. I am passionate about our culture, heritage and the history of this beautiful city and Airbnb has given me the opportunity to share it with our visitors.

name: VINEYARD | BBQ | BEACH 5 MIN | POND | STONE SHOWER
host_about:
Hi, we are Chris, Jen, Toddler Emerson & Baby Madison!

I am a private chef from the East Coast/Italy and my wife is a local/Brit in human rights work!

We have converted our multi-generational Malibu family property into an absolutely stunning Airbnb oasis that is private, stylish, and close to the best beaches, as well as town hot spots (the only shared space is the parking entrance to ensure your upmost privacy is taken care of).

Here you will find a vineyard, orchard, pond, infinity pool, macrame swings, stew grill, hammock, outdoor dining, gazebos, hot tub, Wifi, vintage soaking tub with rain shower, stone walkin shower, smart TVs, fireplaces, high speed wifi, kids toys, central location, celebrity hot spot lookout, easy Uber/DoorDash, private parking, full hotel organic bath+kitchen amenities, secret access to famous state park, beach club additions/clearance, room service, mini-bar, lots of lawn games, firepit tables, tee pee, kayak/paddle-boards, organic vegetable garden & lots more to enjoy! 

We are so happy to open our Malibu oasis for you to enjoy, so anything else we can do to ensure it’s a great stay, just let us know!

Cheers!!!

name: Ivory Room at Casa de Sierra Bonita Room #1
host_about: Welcome to Casa de Sierra Bonita! I am Jed and I live at the house and run this Airbnb. I am a native Angelino who grew up in West Hollywood. I love to go surfing, biking, skating, and hiking. Feel free to ask me for directions, recommendations, or reach out if you have any questions/concerns about your stay. Casa de Sierra Bonita is a large home in the heart of West Hollywood that has several rooms for rent on Airbnb. We have the White and Green Rooms, which come with a full-sized bed that is big enough for two and an attached, full-size, private bathroom. We also have the Bunk Room with which comes with a single-over-full sized bunk bed and access to a semi-private bathroom, which is located just outside the room in the main hallway. Each room comes with private access and is equipped with a mini-fridge for food and drink storage during your stay. Feel free to inquire about renting several rooms in the house for families and larger groups that might be traveling together, or if you plan to book a longer stay. Please note that I am a full-time professional who works in the biotech industry developing novel screens for cancer. I'll do my best to get back to you right away but please understand that my availability may be limited during normal business hours (M - F between 9 am - 6 pm). Lastly, please be aware that we have a lovely little doggo that lives on the property, let me know if you would like to meet or prefer not to interact with her.

name: HAAS // Split Level Loft w/ 2 Queen Beds // DTLA
host_about:
The Haas Building

The Haas Building is located at 219 West 7th Street, at the corner of Broadway and Seventh Street, in Historic Downtown Los Angeles, California. The building was originally owned by Abraham Haas of San Francisco; president of Haas, Baruch, & Company. The structure was made to be one of the finest and most modern buildings of the time. The building was constructed in the year (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) , built with the latest steel frame and absolutely fireproof. Architectural firm Morgan, Walls & Clements designed this 12-story terra cotta business structure attractively facing the street with a frontage of 55 feet (17 m) on Broadway by 150 feet (46 m) on Seventh. The building was 50 by 75 feet (23 m) on the ground floor as well as the basement. The Haas Building was completed early (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) The interior woodwork was made in solid mahogany; the corridors were floored with marble with seven-foot marble wainscoting. The floor, walls and ceiling of the lobby were also made with marble. Including the three high-speed elevators that were installed, fixtures and interiors were said to have cost approximately $ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) ]
The building had been given a complete makeover in the (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) s, with the classic exterior lost to brown metal panels. While much of the exterior brick and detail work was removed, the pieces around the entryway survived, though they were heavily damaged.
The Haas Building has undergone a complete remodel and has 68 live/work lofts. In addition, the top two floors of The Haas Building will be the home of the Haas PH, a multi-functional private event space. The 16,000-square-foot (1,500 m2) space has the feel of a modern boutique hotel with touches of its illustrious 99-year history throughout.
