host_about:
Hi, I'm Jean!

Back in 2014, I moved from Austin to LA to pursue my career in the Food and Agriculture industry. Both cities' diversed and artistic cultures truly capture my heart and I often travel back and forth to visit my friends and family!

I'm friendly, casual, and love to meet new people from around the world. I'm also very passionate in learning new languages and exploring new cultures: Along with English, I speak some Spanish and Vietnamese.

My favorite things in the world are road tripping, gardening, playing piano and collecting cactus. I am also a lover of art, architecture, and interior design. I love nature hence I'm very grateful to call Casa Hazel home, a place of serenity with plenty of greenery and plant species!

I would love to share my beautiful home with guests that also share the love for nature, art, and mid-century-modern design as myself. And I hope my guests will get to experience a true relaxing getaway from the cities to enjoy the beautiful hillside views!

I hope you are happy every day!

We love adventures and extending the beauty of the Santa Monica Mountains to our guests. 
We enjoy hunting for cool items for the house and Tipis and providing little special things for our guests that we also enjoy when we travel. 
We feel so lucky to have the best of all worlds in California- the sand, surf and also the skiing. 
In Californiatipi, we’re off the beaten path with so much peaceful scenery and then so close to the hustle of LA when you want it. 
A % of our Glamping income is donated several of first nation communities.

AirBnb and renting a vacation rental doesn't need to be the unprofessional experience which some may have had in the past. All of our guests will experience a professional operation and I treat every guest and property as if it is a 5 star hotel experience. Professional cleaning crews, quality amenities, 24 hour contact information for myself and team to take care of any needs. In addition I will lend the personal knowledge that I have of Los Angeles to make sure everyone's experience is tailored to their wants and needs. 

I have been traveling and hosting using AirBnb for over 10 years now and consider myself a global citizen of world. With over 30 countries visited and staying in some of the best places (and worst), I strive to make peoples experiences as good as I can when visiting my home city of Los Angeles.

My goal is to make every fellow traveler feel at home in the City of Angels. All of our properties are met with the highest standards of cleanliness, decor, linens, FULLY stocked kitchens for cooking, and basic amenities such as spa quality shampoos and soaps.

I look forward to having you!

Follow us on IG also /laluxurybnb

name: Blue Room at Casa de Sierra Bonita Room #4
host_about: Welcome to Casa de Sierra Bonita! I am Jed and I live at the house and run this Airbnb. I am a native Angelino who grew up in West Hollywood. I love to go surfing, biking, skating, and hiking. Feel free to ask me for directions, recommendations, or reach out if you have any questions/concerns about your stay. Casa de Sierra Bonita is a large home in the heart of West Hollywood that has several rooms for rent on Airbnb. We have the White and Green Rooms, which come with a full-sized bed that is big enough for two and an attached, full-size, private bathroom. We also have the Bunk Room with which comes with a single-over-full sized bunk bed and access to a semi-private bathroom, which is located just outside the room in the main hallway. Each room comes with private access and is equipped with a mini-fridge for food and drink storage during your stay. Feel free to inquire about renting several rooms in the house for families and larger groups that might be traveling together, or if you plan to book a longer stay. Please note that I am a full-time professional who works in the biotech industry developing novel screens for cancer. I'll do my best to get back to you right away but please understand that my availability may be limited during normal business hours (M - F between 9 am - 6 pm). Lastly, please be aware that we have a lovely little doggo that lives on the property, let me know if you would like to meet or prefer not to interact with her.

name: The Cabin 3-Level Loft // Private Patio // Haas
host_about:
The Haas Building

The Haas Building is located at 219 West 7th Street, at the corner of Broadway and Seventh Street, in Historic Downtown Los Angeles, California. The building was originally owned by Abraham Haas of San Francisco; president of Haas, Baruch, & Company. The structure was made to be one of the finest and most modern buildings of the time. The building was constructed in the year (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) , built with the latest steel frame and absolutely fireproof. Architectural firm Morgan, Walls & Clements designed this 12-story terra cotta business structure attractively facing the street with a frontage of 55 feet (17 m) on Broadway by 150 feet (46 m) on Seventh. The building was 50 by 75 feet (23 m) on the ground floor as well as the basement. The Haas Building was completed early (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) The interior woodwork was made in solid mahogany; the corridors were floored with marble with seven-foot marble wainscoting. The floor, walls and ceiling of the lobby were also made with marble. Including the three high-speed elevators that were installed, fixtures and interiors were said to have cost approximately $ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) ]
The building had been given a complete makeover in the (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) s, with the classic exterior lost to brown metal panels. While much of the exterior brick and detail work was removed, the pieces around the entryway survived, though they were heavily damaged.
The Haas Building has undergone a complete remodel and has 68 live/work lofts. In addition, the top two floors of The Haas Building will be the home of the Haas PH, a multi-functional private event space. The 16,000-square-foot (1,500 m2) space has the feel of a modern boutique hotel with touches of its illustrious 99-year history throughout.

name: Malibu Group Tipi Glamping in the Mountains!!
host_about:
Hi, we’re the Ammons family. 
We are avid travelers and have 2 kids that we take with us everywhere we go. 
Tate is from the Tennessee countryside and Andrea is from Alberta, Canada where she grew up alongside the Cree community of Alexander First Nations. 
We love adventures and extending the beauty of the Santa Monica Mountains to our guests. 
We enjoy hunting for cool items for the house and Tipis and providing little special things for our guests that we also enjoy when we travel. 
We feel so lucky to have the best of all worlds in California- the sand, surf and also the skiing. 
In Californiatipi, we’re off the beaten path with so much peaceful scenery and then so close to the hustle of LA when you want it. 
A % of our Glamping income is donated several of first nation communities.

 and I help flip the rooms between guests and I stop by regularly to make sure the house is in order and check to see if you need anything. I like to treat my guests like family and often invite them for dinner, give them a ride, make play dates with their kids, or show them around town!

So please treat my place like your own and keep it clean.  The kitchen, the room, bathroom and living room.  The property has basic wear and tear but it's clean and maintained.  Again, it's not a motel/hotel  so if you are looking for immaculate and perfection, this wouldn't be a good fit.  Pe'Sha is simply somewhere to lay your head and do your thing while traveling.

name: Your home away from home
host_about:
I am a stay-home mom with our 7 yo Amy and 4 yro old Lauren. My husband, Fabian works for LA county as a psychiatrist and we enjoy having guests from around the world, sharing our homes, and exchange experiences, love trying different recipes, and I consider myself real foodies, love to make new friends. 

I was born and raised in Beijing China, lived in South Africa for 5 years during high school, and landed in Las Vegas for the first 8 years before I met Fabian on Eharmony. He is a third generation Mexican, born and raised in Los Angeles, spend his undergraduate years in Las Vegas, medical school New Jersey, and finished his residency in Reno, Nevada. 

We enjoyed traveling together: South Africa, Zimbabwe, Zambia, Russia, Mongolia, China, Japan, Korean, Mexico, Guatemala, Ecuador, Peru, Columbia, Chile, Easter Island, France, Cuba and most recently Costa Rica. Greece, Turkey and Italy, Germany, Czech Republic, and Austria. My husband has been to most part of Europe, Southeast Asia, and South America before we met. Hopefully we can get back to traveling after it’s safe to do so. 

A big thank you to other airbnb hosts and our guests for making all our traveling dreams come true.

host_about:
Hi, my name is LaMonte and I am from the United States.  I gave up my day job to focus on traveling.

I love road trips, it is really the best way to experience whatever area you travel to.  I have taken road trips in four different countries and I hope to experience your country, via road, wherever you are.

Airbnb has given me the wonderful opportunity to provide great times for others.  From the time we connect, to the time we part ways, I get an opportunity to be a part of you having a great experience.  I do aim to please!

I am happy to have several locations near amazing places to visit.  From the ocean, to the desert, to the mountains, you are only 10 to 90 minutes from all of it.  Of course there are major tourist areas like Hollywood, Universal Studios, Disneyland, Sofi Stadium and many more, so come prepared to have a good time!

We loved being able to cook breakfast and have little meals at the cottage, or go to whole foods for fresh, organic meals. The place was so cozy and Dary is excellent at making a small space feel big and comfortable. This place has everything! Great stay and very affordable. You're just moments away from the Venice Beach, great shopping, Gold's Gym, Santa Monica, and much more. When we come back, we plan on booking with Dary again! ”
~Brenna~

“I stayed in this lovely place for several weeks and loved every minute of it. Upon my arrival I found all kinds of surprise goodies which was so generous of Dary. Whenever I had a question or issue, Dary was right there. In addition to an attentive host, i loved the cottage's location - it is safe, private, beautiful, and central to everything. The bed is large and comfortable. The kitchen has all the basics. And the big window is fabulous for light and fresh air. As a bonus, Superba is right around the corner - truly one of LA's best choice for breakfast (pastries and lattes to die for), lunch or dinner. Everyone I met at Dary's was so friendly and interesting. Really, I could not ask for more. This is a great AIRBNB!!! ”
~Tracey~

It was convenient to have a kitchen space with so many cooking basics. The bathroom was very clean and stocked with essentials. It was cold while I was staying but there was a heater and the lofted bed area stayed warm all night. I had an easy time getting to the beach, Hollywood and downtown L.A.. There was always plenty of free parking in front of the home. The little extras Dary provide made the experience exceptional. I highly recommend staying here if you have a chance.”
~ David ~

“This place was adorable. Everything was easy & Dary was very attentive with my questions and with communication. Everything was clean and cozy and I felt safe and happy being there. “Dary was communicative, friendly and an overall great host. The location was great and the apartment was on the back of the house so felt very private even though there were other units close by. “We absolutely loved our stay. We are driving the coast for our honeymoon and after the wedding madness needed a cozy place to stay. We immediately felt at home in this adorable yard and room. ~ Meghan ~ 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

“This is the second time I have stayed with Dary. The location of her rentals in proximity of the beach is FANTASTIC! Abbot Kinney street (with great restaurants and shops) is a close walk away and leads right down to the beach. She makes your stay hassle free by having everything you need and making access to the flat a breeze. Parking is also not an issue if you have a vehicle; there's plenty of free street parking. I would stay with Dary again anytime... and probably will in the future! ”

host_about:
Hello my name is Peter,

I was born and raised in the Mojave desert. I am in my early 30s and I recently left my job as an aircraft mechanic so I could live my dream of travelling the world and seeing the sights with my lovely wife.

I am extremely easy to talk too and really love meeting new people on my adventures. I’ve stayed in Airbnb’s all over the world and have met some great people on the platform who I now call my friends.

My favourite things in this world are basketball, tennis, and computers (hardware, software, and especially video games). I especially love the outdoors and hiking. Oh, and I can't forget, food! All kinds of food but Malaysian food is my favorite and a must try!

I also have a passion for learning new languages which has come in helpful on my travels. Along with English, I speak some German(highschool level), Cantonese, and Mandarin.

Airbnb host Peter Ng

name: Home with Friends (Private Room #2)
host_about:
I love to travel, experience different cultures, meet new people and eat yummy food. My fiancée and our three young daughters (ages 5, 7, & 9) live in Long Beach and we Airbnb three bedrooms in our Inglewood home. 

My friends
 and I help flip the rooms between guests and I stop by regularly to make sure the house is in order and check to see if you need anything. I like to treat my guests like family and often invite them for dinner, give them a ride, make play dates with their kids, or show them around town! 

I spent a decade building custom-made trips/programs for international visitors to LA and California so I know the area and surrounding states well and I am happy to give advice and input on where to go and how best to get there.

name: 1 BR in Central Location with Boutique Amenities
host_about:
Everything we do is designed to give you, the guest, the best possible luxury experience. We have curated, what we believe to be, the best and most comprehensive collection of Luxury Aparthotels created within the most fantastic buildings, located in the most desirable areas for you to enjoy a stay in. 

All our luxury boutique Aparthotels spaces are designed as luxury independent living accommodation within stunning, mostly brand-new, apartment communities around the world, but also operated at the same time as a luxury hotel.  

So, a personal concierge is always at the end of phone, email or SMS / (Hidden by Airbnb) 24/7.  

Daily housekeeping and maid services are always available, extra towels and sheets are but a message away.

Most importantly a One Lux Stay is available to be tailored so you don’t have to think about anything during your stay, perhaps you’d like a fully stocked fridge with all your favourite foods ready for you when you check in, a stocked bar with your favourite tipples, excursions booked, and anything your heart desires that we can only provide.  

Your One Lux apartment is just that, it’s a complete and self-contained, fully furnished and equipped apartment. So, you’ll have a fully equipped kitchen, living space, bedroom and bathroom, each space is designed and equipped for both comfort and luxury, whether you are staying for 1 night or 6 months.  

Our collection of spaces ranges from stunning studios with amazing views to huge 3-bedroom penthouse lofts with exceptional balconies and views and everything in between. 

Every apartment is configured to mirror what you would expect from a luxury hotel – 
Luxury 800+ thread count linens, towels and accessories 
Designer furniture and décor 
Stylish flatware, juicers, coffee machines and blenders 
High-speed Wi-Fi 
Smart TV’s
All utilities are included in a One Lux Stay, regardless of how short or long your stay is going to be. 
All our buildings have secure internal parking available onsite.

To be a One Lux Stay building, our standards are insanely high. Our buildings are designed to create more ‘ (Hidden by Airbnb) -able moments and spaces’ than you could ever post.

You’ll always find – 
Oversized Pool Decks and Spa’s 
A gorgeous rooftop space 
A full and extensive Gym, we aim to also have yoga and or studio space as often as possible 
Co-Working spaces and lounges 
Exceptional outdoor space including outdoor grilles, lounges, firepits and cabanas

name: PRIVATE/GATED LUX 1BD - 1BR Home in West Hollywood
host_about:
Hello,

I grew up in Southern California and am a true LA Native. I am extremely
responsive, reliable, and transparent. I am here to accommodate your needs and make sure your stay is nothing short of great! If you need any recommendations on what to do or see, please let me know and I will gladly help. All of my listings are super clean, well equipped, and optimized for safety. If you have any questions, please feel free to message me. Can’t wait to host you in my home! 

HIGHLIGHTS ON OUR CLEANING PROTOCOLS :
-We sanitize high-touch surfaces, down to the doorknob.
-We use cleaners and disinfectants approved by global health agencies, and we wear protective gear to help prevent cross-contamination. 
-We provide extra cleaning supplies so you can clean as you stay. 
-We comply with local laws, including any additional safety or cleaning guidelines from the Centers for Disease Control.
-We Empower our guests by setting out cleaning supplies they can use.

"Probably my favourite Air BnB in Venice. So convenient. So cool and clean. Unique place with a truly caring and considerate host in Dary. Will 100% stay there again. "

~ Christopher ~
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

“My boyfriend and I really enjoyed our stay in Dary's cottage. It was on a nice, quiet street, yet close to many luxuries. Being into health, having WholeFoods near by was a bonus. We loved being able to cook breakfast and have little meals at the cottage, or go to whole foods for fresh, organic meals. The place was so cozy and Dary is excellent at making a small space feel big and comfortable. This place has everything! Great stay and very affordable. Dary greeted us upon our arrival and made us feel welcome. It's a safe space and very peaceful. You're just moments away from the Venice Beach, great shopping, Gold's Gym, Santa Monica, and much more. When we come back, we plan on booking with Dary again! ”
~Brenna~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

“I stayed in this lovely place for several weeks and loved every minute of it. Upon my arrival I found all kinds of surprise goodies which was so generous of Dary. Whenever I had a question or issue, Dary was right there. In addition to an attentive host, i loved the cottage's location - it is safe, private, beautiful, and central to everything. The bed is large and comfortable. The kitchen has all the basics. And the big window is fabulous for light and fresh air. As a bonus, Superba is right around the corner - truly one of LA's best choice for breakfast (pastries and lattes to die for), lunch or dinner. Everyone I met at Dary's was so friendly and interesting. Really, I could not ask for more. This is a great AIRBNB!!! ”
~Tracey~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Tiki Love Shack
“Dary was a fantastic host. The residence is beautiful and very relaxing. The living space was very cozy. The decor was warm and inviting with an extremely comfortable bed. It was convenient to have a kitchen space with so many cooking basics. The bathroom was very clean and stocked with essentials. It was cold while I was staying but there was a heater and the lofted bed area stayed warm all night. I had an easy time getting to the beach, Hollywood and downtown L.A.. There was always plenty of free parking in front of the home. The little extras Dary provide made the experience exceptional. I highly recommend staying here if you have a chance.”
~ David ~

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

“This place was adorable. Everything was easy & Dary was very attentive with my questions and with communication. Everything was clean and cozy and I felt safe and happy being there. This is perfect for 1-2 people who want to stay in Venice, yet be close to 101 to hit up Marina Del Rey or Santa Monica too. (Quickly) There was outside space to use if needed and extra supplies in the room if you forgot anything. All of the instructions for TV/Internet etc were very easy to understand. I appreciate a nice, clean place to lay my head at night and this was the best experience I've had at an Airbnb location so far! Thanks Dary! I will stay again next time I am in town!”    - Dana - 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

“Dary was communicative, friendly and an overall great host. The location was great and the apartment was on the back of the house so felt very private even though there were other units close by. I would definitely recommend staying here! The unit was so well done, clean and cosy. we loved it! thanks for being a great host. ”    - Martha -

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

“We absolutely loved our stay. We are driving the coast for our honeymoon and after the wedding madness needed a cozy place to stay. We immediately felt at home in this adorable yard and room. Especially loved brewing a pot of coffee and having a slow morning in this quiet adorable place. Thanks Dary!”
~ Meghan ~ 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

“This is the second time I have stayed with Dary. The location of her rentals in proximity of the beach is FANTASTIC! Abbot Kinney street (with great restaurants and shops) is a close walk away and leads right down to the beach. She makes your stay hassle free by having everything you need and making access to the flat a breeze. Parking is also not an issue if you have a vehicle; there's plenty of free street parking. I would stay with Dary again anytime... and probably will in the future! ”
~ Ondrea ~ 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

“Dary's place is absolutely adorable. Secluded, spacious with all the amenities needed. What a gem! ”
~ Jessica ~ 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

“Perfect place for two! This apartment had everything you could need, from minor toiletries to snacks, laundry, cable and wi-fi. A bunch of awesome bicycles and boogie boards were available to use as well as outdoor seating areas and a firepit. The loft was very comfortable and very clean. It was nicely decorated and the entire property was so charming. Dary is an excellent host, and we felt right at home. We look forward to being a repeat visitor and we plan on sending any friends in the area her way too! ”
~Sharon~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

“With Dary´s place I found my perfect place for visiting LA. I will come back for sure! The place is exactly as shown in the pictures. Everthing works and it is all clean. What you cannot see is that the cottage is located in a very nice neighborhood. It is quite, but you are still in the middle of everything. Dary is a wonderful host. She is very friendly, supportive, helpful and always available. ”
~ Hilke ~

name: Furnished 1BR Walk to 3rd St Pier & Beach
host_about:
Everything we do is designed to give you, the guest, the best possible luxury experience. We have curated, what we believe to be, the best and most comprehensive collection of Luxury Aparthotels created within the most fantastic buildings, located in the most desirable areas for you to enjoy a stay in. 

All our luxury boutique Aparthotels spaces are designed as luxury independent living accommodation within stunning, mostly brand-new, apartment communities around the world, but also operated at the same time as a luxury hotel.  

So, a personal concierge is always at the end of phone, email or SMS / (Hidden by Airbnb) 24/7.  

Daily housekeeping and maid services are always available, extra towels and sheets are but a message away.

Most importantly a One Lux Stay is available to be tailored so you don’t have to think about anything during your stay, perhaps you’d like a fully stocked fridge with all your favourite foods ready for you when you check in, a stocked bar with your favourite tipples, excursions booked, and anything your heart desires that we can only provide.  

Your One Lux apartment is just that, it’s a complete and self-contained, fully furnished and equipped apartment. So, you’ll have a fully equipped kitchen, living space, bedroom and bathroom, each space is designed and equipped for both comfort and luxury, whether you are staying for 1 night or 6 months.  

Our collection of spaces ranges from stunning studios with amazing views to huge 3-bedroom penthouse lofts with exceptional balconies and views and everything in between. 

Every apartment is configured to mirror what you would expect from a luxury hotel – 
Luxury 800+ thread count linens, towels and accessories 
Designer furniture and décor 
Stylish flatware, juicers, coffee machines and blenders 
High-speed Wi-Fi 
Smart TV’s
All utilities are included in a One Lux Stay, regardless of how short or long your stay is going to be. 
All our buildings have secure internal parking available onsite.

To be a One Lux Stay building, our standards are insanely high. Our buildings are designed to create more ‘ (Hidden by Airbnb) -able moments and spaces’ than you could ever post.

You’ll always find – 
Oversized Pool Decks and Spa’s 
A gorgeous rooftop space 
A full and extensive Gym, we aim to also have yoga and or studio space as often as possible 
Co-Working spaces and lounges 
Exceptional outdoor space including outdoor grilles, lounges, firepits and cabanas

-We provide extra cleaning supplies so you can clean as you stay. 
-We comply with local laws, including any additional safety or cleaning guidelines from the Centers for Disease Control.
-We Empower our guests by setting out cleaning supplies they can use.

name: Cozy unit on the first floor
host_about:
I am a stay-home mom with our 7 yo Amy and 4 yro old Lauren. My husband, Fabian works for LA county as a psychiatrist and we enjoy having guests from around the world, sharing our homes, and exchange experiences, love trying different recipes, and I consider myself real foodies, love to make new friends. 

I was born and raised in Beijing China, lived in South Africa for 5 years during high school, and landed in Las Vegas for the first 8 years before I met Fabian on Eharmony. He is a third generation Mexican, born and raised in Los Angeles, spend his undergraduate years in Las Vegas, medical school New Jersey, and finished his residency in Reno, Nevada. 

We enjoyed traveling together: South Africa, Zimbabwe, Zambia, Russia, Mongolia, China, Japan, Korean, Mexico, Guatemala, Ecuador, Peru, Columbia, Chile, Easter Island, France, Cuba and most recently Costa Rica. Greece, Turkey and Italy, Germany, Czech Republic, and Austria. My husband has been to most part of Europe, Southeast Asia, and South America before we met. Hopefully we can get back to traveling after it’s safe to do so. 

A big thank you to other airbnb hosts and our guests for making all our traveling dreams come true.

name: Spacious 2BR in the Heart of Glendale
host_about:
Everything we do is designed to give you, the guest, the best possible luxury experience. We have curated, what we believe to be, the best and most comprehensive collection of Luxury Aparthotels created within the most fantastic buildings, located in the most desirable areas for you to enjoy a stay in. 

All our luxury boutique Aparthotels spaces are designed as luxury independent living accommodation within stunning, mostly brand-new, apartment communities around the world, but also operated at the same time as a luxury hotel.  

So, a personal concierge is always at the end of phone, email or SMS / (Hidden by Airbnb) 24/7.  

Daily housekeeping and maid services are always available, extra towels and sheets are but a message away.

Most importantly a One Lux Stay is available to be tailored so you don’t have to think about anything during your stay, perhaps you’d like a fully stocked fridge with all your favourite foods ready for you when you check in, a stocked bar with your favourite tipples, excursions booked, and anything your heart desires that we can only provide.  

Your One Lux apartment is just that, it’s a complete and self-contained, fully furnished and equipped apartment. So, you’ll have a fully equipped kitchen, living space, bedroom and bathroom, each space is designed and equipped for both comfort and luxury, whether you are staying for 1 night or 6 months.  

Our collection of spaces ranges from stunning studios with amazing views to huge 3-bedroom penthouse lofts with exceptional balconies and views and everything in between. 

Every apartment is configured to mirror what you would expect from a luxury hotel – 
Luxury 800+ thread count linens, towels and accessories 
Designer furniture and décor 
Stylish flatware, juicers, coffee machines and blenders 
High-speed Wi-Fi 
Smart TV’s
All utilities are included in a One Lux Stay, regardless of how short or long your stay is going to be. 
All our buildings have secure internal parking available onsite.

To be a One Lux Stay building, our standards are insanely high. Our buildings are designed to create more ‘ (Hidden by Airbnb) -able moments and spaces’ than you could ever post.

You’ll always find – 
Oversized Pool Decks and Spa’s 
A gorgeous rooftop space 
A full and extensive Gym, we aim to also have yoga and or studio space as often as possible 
Co-Working spaces and lounges 
Exceptional outdoor space including outdoor grilles, lounges, firepits and cabanas

host_about: I am a Transaction Coordinator and Legal Assistant in the real estate and legal field.  I am a native of Los Angeles and have traveled extensively in Europe, Australia, Mexico and Canada.  I welcome international travelers!   I'm very laid back and friendly.  I love a big mug of strong coffee in the morning and a glass of cabernet in the evening.  I am a movie buff.  I have worked at various major motion picture studios for 17 years.  I keep HGTV on 24/7 when I'm not watching "The Walking Dead", "Billions", "Power", or the "Real Housewives"!  I love all types of music.  I grew up on the Motown sound, The Beatles, Elvis, Frank Sinatra & Johnny Mathis.  Currently, I love most rap music and most pop music.  I love Kendrick Lamar, Eminem, Lady Ga Ga, Pink!, Ed Sheeran, Bruno Mars, Adele, Maroon 5, Jay Z and Beyonce, to name a few.  I love my family.  Most of my brothers and sisters live nearby.  Some of my favorite restaurants are Javier's in Century City, The Little Kitchen of Italy in Westchester, Ruth Chris, Killer Shrimp, and of course the always reliable Cheesecake Factory in the Marina!  I guess my motto in life is. . .if you don't stand for something, you'll fall for anything.  I stand for human and equal rights.  Do unto others. . .and we'll all be alright!

name: NEW, PRIME SANTA MONICA LUXURY HOME ONE-OF-A-KIND
host_about:
Dear Guests! We always dreamed to live near the ocean and our dream realized 25 years ago when we purchased this home. Over the years, we put lots of efforts to make it comfortable and unique, filled with good vibes and memories. Like most people who discover Santa Monica, for us, it was love at first sight and we hope it will be the same for you. We have recently retired and, in December 2021, we have opened doors of our home to visitors from all over the world. 

The house will tell you a lot about us. 

We love to travel, and we bring a unique picture frame from every country and place we have visited. Dream with us about your next trip looking at this unique display of images from all over the world. 

We love gardening and you can feel it in our one-of-a-kind, oasis, Zen patio that was inspired by the Bel Air Hotel gardens. It has a mixture of natural greenery and artificial plants to cover hard to grow areas, fountain, multiple décor items and handmade Tiffany lights and lanterns. It is just magic!

We love décor. Each room has its own wall decorative finish, such as Venetian plaster, pearl, handmade stencils, custom tiles and faux paints. 

We hope that you will appreciate our art collection by renowned artists - Herman Gold and Anatoly Zaslavsky. Their works are displayed in many museums in Russia and Ukraine, galleries in France, Greece, Israel, the USA, as well as in private collections around the world. 

We love clean and comfortable home and hope you will as well. We thought about many details to make your stay very enjoyable such as Italian towel warmers, chargers on each nightstand, TV in every room, gourmet kitchen, full office, board games and many more. 

We put our hearts and soul to make our guests feel home away from home. We strive to provide you with an outstanding staying experience, and we look forward to hosting you! Let us know if you need anything, please take good care of our home during your stay and come back soon!

name: Sofi / Rams Stadium 10min LAX Beaches aka "Lovely"
host_about:
Pe'Sha is "The Place to Stay".  A relaxing place that's affordable, simple, cozy and very quiet.  

About Your Host:  Hi, I'm Miss very straightforward and direct, in case you can't tell by reading my listings lol.  I have a passion for business, learning new things and helping others.  I am single, no kids except for my Airbnb listings are my babies that's why I gave them names hahaha, and I take good care of them to share with you.  I choose to be HAPPY almost all the time.  I am very honest, ethical and trustworthy.

 I love a good conversation with my guest or just leaving you alone and let you do your thing, unless you are violating my rules then you have to leave. 

MUST READ:

Please take the time to go over the entire profile just one more time.

The Pe'Sha places are NOT Hotels,  I don't charge a cleaning because I wanted to limit my guest cost.  So if you choose to book with me it's mandatory that you clean up behind yourself.  So please treat my place like your own and keep it clean.  The kitchen, the room, bathroom and living room.  The property has basic wear and tear but it's clean and maintained.  Again, it's not a motel/hotel  so if you are looking for immaculate and perfection, this wouldn't be a good fit.  Pe'Sha is simply somewhere to lay your head and do your thing while traveling.

name: Matador by AvantStay | Ocean Front Malibu Pad w/ Rooftop Patio
host_about:
Highly-curated experiences, tailored to guests’ preferences with one-of-a-kind touches, in-home technology and beautiful design. Our experiential homes are crafted, from start to finish, with you in mind.

With 250+ homes in San Diego, Tahoe, Palm Springs, Malibu, Venice, Temecula, Paso Robles, Orange County, Bend, and Scottsdale, we’ve got the perfect place for your next trip and the one after that. Check out our main AvantStay account with 2,000+ reviews! 

What Makes Us Unique:


First Class Amenities  - Enjoy silky linens, plush towels, artisanal soaps and Soothe  massages from the comfort of your home.
Authentic Local Experiences - Discounts on everything from car rentals to wine tasting, and a variety of travel services. 
At Your Service, Always - 24-hour support means that you spend your vacation time enjoying and leave the worrying to us.
Entertainment for Everyone - Outfitted with games and plenty of outdoor activities like pools, jacuzzis, outdoor fire pits and everything for the perfect barbecue. 

How do you top going to a legendary beach town like Malibu? You make your stay with us. We curate the creme de la creme of Malibu’s home experience with our beachfront homes and cliffside villas designed for your every comfort. An unforgettable experience starts here. Welcome to AvantStay Malibu.

Go Together, Go Far.

name: The Study - Unique 5 Bedroom in Downtown LA
host_about:
The Haas Building

The Haas Building is located at 219 West 7th Street, at the corner of Broadway and Seventh Street, in Historic Downtown Los Angeles, California. The building was originally owned by Abraham Haas of San Francisco; president of Haas, Baruch, & Company. The structure was made to be one of the finest and most modern buildings of the time. The building was constructed in the year (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) , built with the latest steel frame and absolutely fireproof. Architectural firm Morgan, Walls & Clements designed this 12-story terra cotta business structure attractively facing the street with a frontage of 55 feet (17 m) on Broadway by 150 feet (46 m) on Seventh. The building was 50 by 75 feet (23 m) on the ground floor as well as the basement. The Haas Building was completed early (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) The interior woodwork was made in solid mahogany; the corridors were floored with marble with seven-foot marble wainscoting. The floor, walls and ceiling of the lobby were also made with marble. Including the three high-speed elevators that were installed, fixtures and interiors were said to have cost approximately $ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) ]
The building had been given a complete makeover in the (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) s, with the classic exterior lost to brown metal panels. While much of the exterior brick and detail work was removed, the pieces around the entryway survived, though they were heavily damaged.
The Haas Building has undergone a complete remodel and has 68 live/work lofts. In addition, the top two floors of The Haas Building will be the home of the Haas PH, a multi-functional private event space. The 16,000-square-foot (1,500 m2) space has the feel of a modern boutique hotel with touches of its illustrious 99-year history throughout.

I am a stay-home mom with our 7 yo Amy and 4 yro old Lauren. My husband, Fabian works for LA county as a psychiatrist and we enjoy having guests from around the world, sharing our homes, and exchange experiences, love trying different recipes, and I consider myself real foodies, love to make new friends. 

I was born and raised in Beijing China, lived in South Africa for 5 years during high school, and landed in Las Vegas for the first 8 years before I met Fabian on Eharmony. He is a third generation Mexican, born and raised in Los Angeles, spend his undergraduate years in Las Vegas, medical school New Jersey, and finished his residency in Reno, Nevada. 

We enjoyed traveling together: South Africa, Zimbabwe, Zambia, Russia, Mongolia, China, Japan, Korean, Mexico, Guatemala, Ecuador, Peru, Columbia, Chile, Easter Island, France, Cuba and most recently Costa Rica. name: Downtown Glendale 2BR: Gym, Pool, Spa
host_about:
Everything we do is designed to give you, the guest, the best possible luxury experience. We have curated, what we believe to be, the best and most comprehensive collection of Luxury Aparthotels created within the most fantastic buildings, located in the most desirable areas for you to enjoy a stay in. 

All our luxury boutique Aparthotels spaces are designed as luxury independent living accommodation within stunning, mostly brand-new, apartment communities around the world, but also operated at the same time as a luxury hotel.  

So, a personal concierge is always at the end of phone, email or SMS / (Hidden by Airbnb) 24/7.  

Daily housekeeping and maid services are always available, extra towels and sheets are but a message away.

Most importantly a One Lux Stay is available to be tailored so you don’t have to think about anything during your stay, perhaps you’d like a fully stocked fridge with all your favourite foods ready for you when you check in, a stocked bar with your favourite tipples, excursions booked, and anything your heart desires that we can only provide.  

Your One Lux apartment is just that, it’s a complete and self-contained, fully furnished and equipped apartment. So, you’ll have a fully equipped kitchen, living space, bedroom and bathroom, each space is designed and equipped for both comfort and luxury, whether you are staying for 1 night or 6 months.  

Our collection of spaces ranges from stunning studios with amazing views to huge 3-bedroom penthouse lofts with exceptional balconies and views and everything in between. 

Every apartment is configured to mirror what you would expect from a luxury hotel – 
Luxury 800+ thread count linens, towels and accessories 
Designer furniture and décor 
Stylish flatware, juicers, coffee machines and blenders 
High-speed Wi-Fi 
Smart TV’s
All utilities are included in a One Lux Stay, regardless of how short or long your stay is going to be. 
All our buildings have secure internal parking available onsite.

To be a One Lux Stay building, our standards are insanely high. Our buildings are designed to create more ‘ (Hidden by Airbnb) -able moments and spaces’ than you could ever post.

You’ll always find – 
Oversized Pool Decks and Spa’s 
A gorgeous rooftop space 
A full and extensive Gym, we aim to also have yoga and or studio space as often as possible 
Co-Working spaces and lounges 
Exceptional outdoor space including outdoor grilles, lounges, firepits and cabanas

name: Green Room at Casa de Sierra Bonita #3
host_about: Welcome to Casa de Sierra Bonita! I am Jed and I live at the house and run this Airbnb. I am a native Angelino who grew up in West Hollywood. I love to go surfing, biking, skating, and hiking. Feel free to ask me for directions, recommendations, or reach out if you have any questions/concerns about your stay. Casa de Sierra Bonita is a large home in the heart of West Hollywood that has several rooms for rent on Airbnb. We have the White and Green Rooms, which come with a full-sized bed that is big enough for two and an attached, full-size, private bathroom. We also have the Bunk Room with which comes with a single-over-full sized bunk bed and access to a semi-private bathroom, which is located just outside the room in the main hallway. Each room comes with private access and is equipped with a mini-fridge for food and drink storage during your stay. Feel free to inquire about renting several rooms in the house for families and larger groups that might be traveling together, or if you plan to book a longer stay. Please note that I am a full-time professional who works in the biotech industry developing novel screens for cancer. I'll do my best to get back to you right away but please understand that my availability may be limited during normal business hours (M - F between 9 am - 6 pm). Lastly, please be aware that we have a lovely little doggo that lives on the property, let me know if you would like to meet or prefer not to interact with her.

name: DTLA HISTORIC HIGH TECH 1BR, POOL, JACUZZI & GYM
host_about:
Everything we do is designed to give you, the guest, the best possible luxury experience. We have curated, what we believe to be, the best and most comprehensive collection of Luxury Aparthotels created within the most fantastic buildings, located in the most desirable areas for you to enjoy a stay in. 

All our luxury boutique Aparthotels spaces are designed as luxury independent living accommodation within stunning, mostly brand-new, apartment communities around the world, but also operated at the same time as a luxury hotel.  

So, a personal concierge is always at the end of phone, email or SMS / (Hidden by Airbnb) 24/7.  

Daily housekeeping and maid services are always available, extra towels and sheets are but a message away.

Most importantly a One Lux Stay is available to be tailored so you don’t have to think about anything during your stay, perhaps you’d like a fully stocked fridge with all your favourite foods ready for you when you check in, a stocked bar with your favourite tipples, excursions booked, and anything your heart desires that we can only provide.  

Your One Lux apartment is just that, it’s a complete and self-contained, fully furnished and equipped apartment. So, you’ll have a fully equipped kitchen, living space, bedroom and bathroom, each space is designed and equipped for both comfort and luxury, whether you are staying for 1 night or 6 months.  

Our collection of spaces ranges from stunning studios with amazing views to huge 3-bedroom penthouse lofts with exceptional balconies and views and everything in between. 

Every apartment is configured to mirror what you would expect from a luxury hotel – 
Luxury 800+ thread count linens, towels and accessories 
Designer furniture and décor 
Stylish flatware, juicers, coffee machines and blenders 
High-speed Wi-Fi 
Smart TV’s
All utilities are included in a One Lux Stay, regardless of how short or long your stay is going to be. 
All our buildings have secure internal parking available onsite.

To be a One Lux Stay building, our standards are insanely high. Our buildings are designed to create more ‘ (Hidden by Airbnb) -able moments and spaces’ than you could ever post.

You’ll always find – 
Oversized Pool Decks and Spa’s 
A gorgeous rooftop space 
A full and extensive Gym, we aim to also have yoga and or studio space as often as possible 
Co-Working spaces and lounges 
Exceptional outdoor space including outdoor grilles, lounges, firepits and cabanas

name: **NEW DESIGNER TOWNHOUSE WALKING TO UNIVERSAL!**
host_about:
AirBnb and renting a vacation rental doesn't need to be the unprofessional experience which some may have had in the past. All of our guests will experience a professional operation and I treat every guest and property as if it is a 5 star hotel experience. Professional cleaning crews, quality amenities, 24 hour contact information for myself and team to take care of any needs. In addition I will lend the personal knowledge that I have of Los Angeles to make sure everyone's experience is tailored to their wants and needs. 

I have been traveling and hosting using AirBnb for over 10 years now and consider myself a global citizen of world. With over 30 countries visited and staying in some of the best places (and worst), I strive to make peoples experiences as good as I can when visiting my home city of Los Angeles.

My goal is to make every fellow traveler feel at home in the City of Angels. All of our properties are met with the highest standards of cleanliness, decor, linens, FULLY stocked kitchens for cooking, and basic amenities such as spa quality shampoos and soaps.

I look forward to having you!

Follow us on IG also /laluxurybnb

The PERFECT middle between Culver City, Venice, Marina Del Ray, Santa Monica, and West Hollywood areas!

Please check out our LOCATIONS: 

Our FIRST listing is a beautiful ENTIRE studio apartment with PATIO in Culver City, near the Sony Pictures studio, not far from VENICE, MARINA DEL RAY, AND LAX.




The SECOND is a SEMI-PRIVATE LIVING ROOM with a QUEEN size bed. 
NO DOORS to be locked.

OWNER is in the apartment.

name: "GrAce - LAX, Sofi 25mins - Beach 10mins - Hikes
host_about:
Pe'Sha is "The Place to Stay".  A relaxing place that's affordable, simple, cozy and very quiet.  

About Your Host:  Hi, I'm Miss very straightforward and direct, in case you can't tell by reading my listings lol.  I have a passion for business, learning new things and helping others.  I am single, no kids except for my Airbnb listings are my babies that's why I gave them names hahaha, and I take good care of them to share with you.  I choose to be HAPPY almost all the time.  I am very honest, ethical and trustworthy.

 I love a good conversation with my guest or just leaving you alone and let you do your thing, unless you are violating my rules then you have to leave. 

MUST READ:

Please take the time to go over the entire profile just one more time.

The Pe'Sha places are NOT Hotels,  I don't charge a cleaning because I wanted to limit my guest cost.  So if you choose to book with me it's mandatory that you clean up behind yourself.  So please treat my place like your own and keep it clean.  The kitchen, the room, bathroom and living room.  The property has basic wear and tear but it's clean and maintained.  Again, it's not a motel/hotel  so if you are looking for immaculate and perfection, this wouldn't be a good fit.  Pe'Sha is simply somewhere to lay your head and do your thing while traveling.

name: Historic DTLA Junior 1BR with Rooftop Gym, Pool
host_about:
Everything we do is designed to give you, the guest, the best possible luxury experience. We have curated, what we believe to be, the best and most comprehensive collection of Luxury Aparthotels created within the most fantastic buildings, located in the most desirable areas for you to enjoy a stay in. 

All our luxury boutique Aparthotels spaces are designed as luxury independent living accommodation within stunning, mostly brand-new, apartment communities around the world, but also operated at the same time as a luxury hotel.  

So, a personal concierge is always at the end of phone, email or SMS / (Hidden by Airbnb) 24/7.  

Daily housekeeping and maid services are always available, extra towels and sheets are but a message away.

Most importantly a One Lux Stay is available to be tailored so you don’t have to think about anything during your stay, perhaps you’d like a fully stocked fridge with all your favourite foods ready for you when you check in, a stocked bar with your favourite tipples, excursions booked, and anything your heart desires that we can only provide.  

Your One Lux apartment is just that, it’s a complete and self-contained, fully furnished and equipped apartment. So, you’ll have a fully equipped kitchen, living space, bedroom and bathroom, each space is designed and equipped for both comfort and luxury, whether you are staying for 1 night or 6 months.  

Our collection of spaces ranges from stunning studios with amazing views to huge 3-bedroom penthouse lofts with exceptional balconies and views and everything in between. 

Every apartment is configured to mirror what you would expect from a luxury hotel – 
Luxury 800+ thread count linens, towels and accessories 
Designer furniture and décor 
Stylish flatware, juicers, coffee machines and blenders 
High-speed Wi-Fi 
Smart TV’s
All utilities are included in a One Lux Stay, regardless of how short or long your stay is going to be. 
All our buildings have secure internal parking available onsite.

To be a One Lux Stay building, our standards are insanely high. Our buildings are designed to create more ‘ (Hidden by Airbnb) -able moments and spaces’ than you could ever post.

You’ll always find – 
Oversized Pool Decks and Spa’s 
A gorgeous rooftop space 
A full and extensive Gym, we aim to also have yoga and or studio space as often as possible 
Co-Working spaces and lounges 
Exceptional outdoor space including outdoor grilles, lounges, firepits and cabanas

name: **NEW 2BR DESIGNER TOWNHOUSE WALK 2 UNIVERSAL!**
host_about:
AirBnb and renting a vacation rental doesn't need to be the unprofessional experience which some may have had in the past. All of our guests will experience a professional operation and I treat every guest and property as if it is a 5 star hotel experience. Professional cleaning crews, quality amenities, 24 hour contact information for myself and team to take care of any needs. In addition I will lend the personal knowledge that I have of Los Angeles to make sure everyone's experience is tailored to their wants and needs. 

I have been traveling and hosting using AirBnb for over 10 years now and consider myself a global citizen of world. With over 30 countries visited and staying in some of the best places (and worst), I strive to make peoples experiences as good as I can when visiting my home city of Los Angeles.

My goal is to make every fellow traveler feel at home in the City of Angels. All of our properties are met with the highest standards of cleanliness, decor, linens, FULLY stocked kitchens for cooking, and basic amenities such as spa quality shampoos and soaps.

I look forward to having you!

Follow us on IG also /laluxurybnb

name: Delightful, 2022 trailer, private & 360 views!
host_about:
Hi, I am English but live in California. I am all about the outdoors..... I love to walk and horse ride, my greatest passions are animals and music.  I'm very social, and adventurous. I also love to go out, eat out, cook, read, learn about history, architecture, anthropology. Music is what gets me by in life! And I love to dance!!!! I studied Classics  and Anthropology. 
I now run my own Pet Care business in Malibu. In 2021 I bought the ranch now known as Wild Horizon Farm. I have hosted for Airbnb previously, but this is where my accommodations are located. In Lake Hughes CA. It's been an incredible and challenging journey to get to this point. A ranch is ENDLESS work. There are horses, pigs, goats and other animals at the property. Its my dream to create a sanctuary for the animals but also - our guests. When you book you are supporting that, and the care of many of the rescue animals - so thank you!

host_about:
A traveler at heart! Before sharing this space with other fellow travelers, I have been to New Zealand, Australia, Maldives, Thailand, Japan, China, United Kingdom, Peru, and Mexico. host_about:
Hello,

I grew up in Southern California and am a true LA Native. I am extremely
responsive, reliable, and transparent. I am here to accommodate your needs and make sure your stay is nothing short of great! If you need any recommendations on what to do or see, please let me know and I will gladly help. All of my listings are super clean, well equipped, and optimized for safety. If you have any questions, please feel free to message me. Can’t wait to host you in my home! 

HIGHLIGHTS ON OUR CLEANING PROTOCOLS :
-We sanitize high-touch surfaces, down to the doorknob.
-We use cleaners and disinfectants approved by global health agencies, and we wear protective gear to help prevent cross-contamination. 
-We provide extra cleaning supplies so you can clean as you stay. 
-We comply with local laws, including any additional safety or cleaning guidelines from the Centers for Disease Control.
-We Empower our guests by setting out cleaning supplies they can use.

AirBnb and renting a vacation rental doesn't need to be the unprofessional experience which some may have had in the past. All of our guests will experience a professional operation and I treat every guest and property as if it is a 5 star hotel experience. Professional cleaning crews, quality amenities, 24 hour contact information for myself and team to take care of any needs. In addition I will lend the personal knowledge that I have of Los Angeles to make sure everyone's experience is tailored to their wants and needs. 

I have been traveling and hosting using AirBnb for over 10 years now and consider myself a global citizen of world. With over 30 countries visited and staying in some of the best places (and worst), I strive to make peoples experiences as good as I can when visiting my home city of Los Angeles.

My goal is to make every fellow traveler feel at home in the City of Angels. All of our properties are met with the highest standards of cleanliness, decor, linens, FULLY stocked kitchens for cooking, and basic amenities such as spa quality shampoos and soaps.

My goal is to make every fellow traveler feel at home in the City of Angels. All of our properties are met with the highest standards of cleanliness, decor, linens, FULLY stocked kitchens for cooking, and basic amenities such as spa quality shampoos and soaps.

-We Empower our guests by setting out cleaning supplies they can use.

name: Historic DTLA 2BR1B with Rooftop Gym, Pool
host_about:
Everything we do is designed to give you, the guest, the best possible luxury experience. We have curated, what we believe to be, the best and most comprehensive collection of Luxury Aparthotels created within the most fantastic buildings, located in the most desirable areas for you to enjoy a stay in. 

All our luxury boutique Aparthotels spaces are designed as luxury independent living accommodation within stunning, mostly brand-new, apartment communities around the world, but also operated at the same time as a luxury hotel.  

So, a personal concierge is always at the end of phone, email or SMS / (Hidden by Airbnb) 24/7.  

Daily housekeeping and maid services are always available, extra towels and sheets are but a message away.

Most importantly a One Lux Stay is available to be tailored so you don’t have to think about anything during your stay, perhaps you’d like a fully stocked fridge with all your favourite foods ready for you when you check in, a stocked bar with your favourite tipples, excursions booked, and anything your heart desires that we can only provide.  

Your One Lux apartment is just that, it’s a complete and self-contained, fully furnished and equipped apartment. So, you’ll have a fully equipped kitchen, living space, bedroom and bathroom, each space is designed and equipped for both comfort and luxury, whether you are staying for 1 night or 6 months.  

Our collection of spaces ranges from stunning studios with amazing views to huge 3-bedroom penthouse lofts with exceptional balconies and views and everything in between. 

Every apartment is configured to mirror what you would expect from a luxury hotel – 
Luxury 800+ thread count linens, towels and accessories 
Designer furniture and décor 
Stylish flatware, juicers, coffee machines and blenders 
High-speed Wi-Fi 
Smart TV’s
All utilities are included in a One Lux Stay, regardless of how short or long your stay is going to be. 
All our buildings have secure internal parking available onsite.

To be a One Lux Stay building, our standards are insanely high. Our buildings are designed to create more ‘ (Hidden by Airbnb) -able moments and spaces’ than you could ever post.

You’ll always find – 
Oversized Pool Decks and Spa’s 
A gorgeous rooftop space 
A full and extensive Gym, we aim to also have yoga and or studio space as often as possible 
Co-Working spaces and lounges 
Exceptional outdoor space including outdoor grilles, lounges, firepits and cabanas

host_about:
I am a wife, mom, grandma, former teacher, and Girl Scout leader who fell into property management and am loving it! I have managed vacation rentals for over ten years now and love helping  make memorable vacations for our guests. My team includes my retired enginerd husband (retirement is VERY busy for him!), our daughters Candace (Law  Enforcement officer) and Kelsey (RN), our grandkids Colson ( (Hidden by Airbnb) poster) and Cadence (product sales), and  my former 4th grade student Caitlynn who is now young lady majoring in Hospitality at Cal Poly Pomona. Our 7 and 4 year old granddaughters are test pilots giving me their input on sand boxes, swing sets, play houses, toys, etc. at various cabins. 
My folks were immigrants from Sweden and Argentina and you will see that flavor come through in the decorating of some of the cabins I manage. Customer service is extremely important to us and we make every effort to accommodate our guests and go above and beyond what guests are used to. I personally love recommendations from locals when visiting some place new, so I give lots of recommendations to my guests.
I appreciate you finding us here on Airbnb and I look forward to hosting you and your respectful family and friends!

name: A 🥰 Sand 🏖 Room @ Homestay 🏡 Near Beach 🏄 & ✈️
host_about:
A BIG WELCOME TO OUR HOME OF SUN, SAND, SURF, SAIL & SEA! 

We hope this will be your home away from home for you when you stay with us.  Our reviews speak for us:-).

MEET YOUR HOSTS: 

We are an Australian Vietnamese American family of 4 who have been enjoying hosting our guests from all over the world in our homes for 17 years. We have been Airbnb hosts since 2012 and Superhost since the program started. We were also awarded Outstanding Travelers’ Award by other platforms since 2019. Booking guests rated us as high as 9.1/10 and even higher that some five star hotels in the area. We genuinely love people and we are world travelers who believe that hosting and traveling will open people’s hearts, minds & souls and ultimately make the world a better place. 

ABOUT COSTA MESA: Do you know that Costa Mesa is the City of the Art & home for Orange County’s top rated restaurants? It’s a mecca for foodies, adventures seekers and fun loving families. The amenities are top notch and all are within 10-20 minute walk or drive.

LOCATION & PROXIMITY: Our listings are right in the heart of Costa Mesa and Orange County and conveniently located near Newport Beach, Huntington Beach, Balboa Island, Corona Del Mar, UCI, Disneyland and the main freeways to Los Angeles, San Diego and San Bernardino mountains.

SHARING & PRIVACY:  This is a shared home so we live on the property and we can have multiple guests at one time. All the guests have their private rooms and private spaces as well as access to the two bathrooms and communal areas. Please click on our profile to see our other listings. We also help with co-hosting. 

CLEANLINESS:

As we have multiple guests, two well mannered rambunctious growing boys ( 14 and 11 years old) and a busy schedule, our house won’t be immaculate like a hotel at all times. You will see our personal belongings in the communal areas and in our own rooms. However, you are assured that we make every effort to ensure your rooms are cleaned and made with fresh & crisp bedding & the bathrooms are attended frequently. 

HOMESTAY VS HOTEL EXPECTATIONS:

You will be staying in a Homestay, means that this is our home in which we are renting out private rooms and spaces to our guests so yes, you will be sharing with other people including us the hosts. On average, there will be 4 of us and there may be 3 or 4 more people depending how many are booked in our 2 other rooms and backyard facilities. 

We are attentive and love to ensure our guests needs are met so we will respond to your requests as soon as we are available. If we don’t meet any of your 5 star expectations, please bring to our attention immediately so we can address it sooner than later. We want to be your 5 star hosts, we really do!

If you want your own bathroom, don’t like meeting people or have expectations of a hotel, our place may not be the best fit for you.

If you love meeting people, exploring local attractions, enjoy our hospitality and don’t mind sharing the bathrooms with others, you are in right place:-). 

Looking forward to hosting you! 

Thơ & Row Costa Mesa

name: Cozy & Bright w Private Bathroom, at The Cottage
host_about:
Nico is a Lifestyle Guide and Gratitude Activist!

Her journey has taken her from a quirky upbringing in small town New Jersey, to a home base in Harlem while butlering around the world. She left it all on a one-way ticket to Bali, in search to find not how much she could have, but how much she could offer. 

She is the Founder of Agape Everyday, a 5-min gratitude mediation, recently ranked in the top 3% of Apple Podcasts. Bali offered her a place to call home for 3-years, guiding yoga and meditation to all groups, from nudists in her treehouse to orphanages in the villages and bringing water filters to those in need.

Her current work bridges the gap between Eastern philosophies and Western lifestyles, creating value through awareness of all that is present.

Her biggest passions include reading, writing, cooking for friends, yoga on the patio and hosting amazing guests in her California mountain home.

name: Bear Mt. “Lodge” 5 Star Private 12 guests 4Br 4Ba
host_about: Your host JC that’s me, loves the outdoors, taking walks in the mountains, skiing, fishing, cooking in our gourmet kitchen, BBQ grilling on the huge deck all right here at Bear Mt Lodge. It is so satisfying to have guest experience this unique place, and to hear about their stories, and the best part is to have shared a taste of our natural environment setting to sense, and feel what I do every day is awesome! I really appreciate rustic log, and rock architecture. The lodge is a unique fusion of European mountain chateau design, my dream come true to have designed and built this lodge, I am truly blessed. My eclectic taste in music brings life, and listening pleasure. It is all part of the mood, from Spanish guitar, new age sounds, top 40, Instrumentals, including Gospel, and so many more are all artistic expression, an art form, creative, and spiritually  inspirational to me.  In the Great room a place I have enjoyed reading many books. To read by the embers of the wood burning stove, or listing to the frogs croaking in the pond through the open windows is so relaxing. Durning a snow storm, drinking a hot chocolate, or sitting on the deck on a late summers making s’mores, and taking in the celestial night sky. Watching a quality movies in the digital Ram room, is a great place to kick back , and I have enjoyed spending many entertaining hours. The third floor has all my favorites in this incredible game room so many friends, and family have hung out playing pool, cards, or one of the many entertaining things to do that I have collected over the years. As you can guess by now why It is so intriguing in this place that is so peaceful,  serene, and nobody wants to leave, and to hear we are coming back for sure is so gratifying to me. So find out for yourself on your first retreat or the next time you come back, there is always something new to experience in my favorite place.

name: 1972 Classic Airstream In  Santa Monica Mountains
host_about:
My husband Chris introduced me to Montana 7 years ago when at about the same time, we discovered the beautiful Wilma. We fell in love with the building and bought our lovely view condo. We don’t get to spend nearly as much time as we would like to there!

We spend most of our time at our ranch in Westlake Village California in the Santa Monica Mountains where I manage our 2 AirbnB’s there as well. One is a beautiful Vintage Airstream and the other is a luxury Conestoga Covered Wagon! Being at Prospector Ranch is like stepping back in time to the 1800’s. We even have a saloon at the ranch! Our lives there keep us quite busy so escaping to The Wilma and Montana is a real treat. We hope you enjoy it as much as we do!

host_about:
I am a wife, mom, grandma, former teacher, and Girl Scout leader who fell into property management and am loving it! I have managed vacation rentals for over ten years now and love helping  make memorable vacations for our guests. My team includes my retired enginerd husband (retirement is VERY busy for him!), our daughters Candace (Law  Enforcement officer) and Kelsey (RN), our grandkids Colson ( (Hidden by Airbnb) poster) and Cadence (product sales), and  my former 4th grade student Caitlynn who is now young lady majoring in Hospitality at Cal Poly Pomona. Our 7 and 4 year old granddaughters are test pilots giving me their input on sand boxes, swing sets, play houses, toys, etc. at various cabins. 
My folks were immigrants from Sweden and Argentina and you will see that flavor come through in the decorating of some of the cabins I manage. Customer service is extremely important to us and we make every effort to accommodate our guests and go above and beyond what guests are used to. I personally love recommendations from locals when visiting some place new, so I give lots of recommendations to my guests.
I appreciate you finding us here on Airbnb and I look forward to hosting you and your respectful family and friends!

name: 5 acre Malibu nature stay, 6 miles from the ocean!
host_about:
We’re Malibu & Joshua Tree living nature lovers. 
    Our Malibu Hideaway on 5.5 acres & surrounded by thousands of acres of open space in the canyons allows us to live in the kind of place we used to seek to find balance & happiness. 
    Being able to share our spaces with like-minded folks brings us happiness! We hope it will bring others as much zen & center as it has us. 
    In silence we hear the trees rustle, the owls hoot and the roosters call. In the evenings the stars gleam so bright & the shooting stars light the nights sky. 
    Before living in the “wild” we would often escape the city for the simplicity we often craved. It’s not uncommon here for us to see Bob-cats, hawks, bunnies, squirrels, scorpions, & so many beautiful birds & creatures. At The Casita the sound of coyotes howling in the night sets the tone. 
    We decided to purchase The Desert Casita on 1.18 acres for the same calm nature-rich environment. Our Desert Casita like Malibu Hideaway is a special place to reset and renew the spirit. 
    The desolate energy of the desert offers so much hidden life and mystery! Every time we’ve escaped to the Mojave desert and submerged in her vitality we have always returned renewed, revitalized, and freshly creative. 
    The High desert like Malibu is a special place on earth that we feel utterly grateful to inhabit and share its magic with others. 
    We have a passion for cooking for our friends & family. We also enjoy the finest cuisines from the best restaurants locally & around the world. 
    We’re both culturally diverse through travel to some of the most beautiful places around the world. 
    Angie is an optimistic, free-spirited, artist & realtor California native. Martin, an artsy, musician, incredible chef, agriculturalist, trilingual French native.
    We love the outdoors and the simple things in life. We enjoy growing our own fruits and veggies, out- door movies in the park, old cemeteries, art & history, natural hot springs, hiking, yoga, beach camping, paddle boarding, biking & fishing. 
We have an affinity to water... rivers, creeks,  brooks, water falls, lakes and beach’s.

name: Bear "Creek" studio
host_about: Your host JC that’s me, loves the outdoors, taking walks in the mountains, skiing, fishing, cooking in our gourmet kitchen, BBQ grilling on the huge deck all right here at Bear Mt Lodge. It is so satisfying to have guest experience this unique place, and to hear about their stories, and the best part is to have shared a taste of our natural environment setting to sense, and feel what I do every day is awesome! I really appreciate rustic log, and rock architecture. The lodge is a unique fusion of European mountain chateau design, my dream come true to have designed and built this lodge, I am truly blessed. My eclectic taste in music brings life, and listening pleasure. It is all part of the mood, from Spanish guitar, new age sounds, top 40, Instrumentals, including Gospel, and so many more are all artistic expression, an art form, creative, and spiritually  inspirational to me.  In the Great room a place I have enjoyed reading many books. To read by the embers of the wood burning stove, or listing to the frogs croaking in the pond through the open windows is so relaxing. Durning a snow storm, drinking a hot chocolate, or sitting on the deck on a late summers making s’mores, and taking in the celestial night sky. Watching a quality movies in the digital Ram room, is a great place to kick back , and I have enjoyed spending many entertaining hours. The third floor has all my favorites in this incredible game room so many friends, and family have hung out playing pool, cards, or one of the many entertaining things to do that I have collected over the years. As you can guess by now why It is so intriguing in this place that is so peaceful,  serene, and nobody wants to leave, and to hear we are coming back for sure is so gratifying to me. So find out for yourself on your first retreat or the next time you come back, there is always something new to experience in my favorite place.

host_about:
Welcome! I love my home & living on the beach in Malibu. I’ve been in Malibu more than 30 years & it’s been incredible! I love to travel & can afford it by renting my house out to people for vacations, shoots & small events! When I travel I enjoy other people’s Airbnb’s & learn new ways all the time on how to make my guests vacations more enjoyable! Sharone

name: BEST OF THE BEST CLOSE TO BEACHES/DISNEYLAND, MORE
host_about:
Hello there! I know that you will love it here.
I have lived here in Mission Viejo my whole life. It is a beautiful  well maintained  very clean City. It is known as the safest city in California.  Many great memories. I love that I get to live by the beach yet have the privacy needed, too! . I take pride in constantly upgrading and beautifying your stay. . It is very quiet very very clean and private and there is everything you need like home. The bed is a new mattress  boxspring and frame, we also added a beautiful topper that is so comfortable. . We try to  keep everything as possible, non-toxic, allergen-free,  all bedding and linens are freashly supplied after each guest leaves. Non-toxic  soaps shampoos and conditioners available. All towels, sheets and all linens are washed with  non-toxic soap. We also have a juice machine available. And we can  answer any questions or concerns you may have. If there is anything you need just ask. Our Motto is treat everyone the way you would like to be treated. We are only about 10 minutes from Laguna Beach We are in a wonderful location the garden studio feels secluded surrounded by trees and flowers plants, and perhaps three minutes from everything everybody loves it here Market restaurants entertainment all over everywhere. Also trails for hiking everything our hearts desire is here and we would love to have you. See you soon!

The free WIFI is nice and strong.

name: Spacious 2BR/2BA! Great amenities! Easy access!
host_about:
Hello...I'm Michael, we provides furnished, turn-key housing to those who need to be away from their permanent base or a vacation get away.  

Whether it's an overnight escape, a week to recharge or long term while on assignment, a home remodel, a residence while your new home is in escrow...

We focus on making your stay as comfortable and worry-free as possible by providing stylish, upscale housing and amenities with concierge-like services, like household essentials brought to your door.

host_about: I love to travel and see the world. I love to meet people who are coming to my house from around the world.

name: Private Entry Suite by Disneyland Park & Knotts
host_about:
Myself, my partner Elysia (both vaccinated) and our pup Skye, live in a quiet and safe neighborhood in the city of La Palma and often work remotely. We stay mindful of our volume and are intentional about our steps, though you may hear us around the home as you would in shared wall apartments or hotels. We have made every effort to insulate the space.

 We are happy to share our home with travelers looking for a safe, private, cozy, convenient, and welcoming space during their stay, whether it be for work or leisure.

We are both Orange County born and raised. We love to travel and explore the world. We enjoy hiking, long walks, beach bonfires and road trips. We encourage our guests to explore and can provide ample suggestions if asked.

Important to note* Skye, our friendly 10lb Schnoodle, is still learning what Airbnb is, so she may be a little curious about the new smells and sounds. So although most of her day is spent napping inside the house, she may vocally greet you or try to sniff around the perimeter of the privacy screens. She simply just wants to say hi and put a face to the sounds/smells, but has No access to you.

You can expect quick and clear communication, and a very clean, private, and tidy space. We hope to provide you with the most relaxing and stress-free experience!

name: A 🥰 Sun ☀️ Room inHomestay - Airport, Beaches & Fun
host_about:
A BIG WELCOME TO OUR HOME OF SUN, SAND, SURF, SAIL & SEA! 

We hope this will be your home away from home for you when you stay with us.  Our reviews speak for us:-).

MEET YOUR HOSTS: 

We are an Australian Vietnamese American family of 4 who have been enjoying hosting our guests from all over the world in our homes for 17 years. We have been Airbnb hosts since 2012 and Superhost since the program started. We were also awarded Outstanding Travelers’ Award by other platforms since 2019. Booking guests rated us as high as 9.1/10 and even higher that some five star hotels in the area. We genuinely love people and we are world travelers who believe that hosting and traveling will open people’s hearts, minds & souls and ultimately make the world a better place. 

ABOUT COSTA MESA: Do you know that Costa Mesa is the City of the Art & home for Orange County’s top rated restaurants? It’s a mecca for foodies, adventures seekers and fun loving families. The amenities are top notch and all are within 10-20 minute walk or drive.

LOCATION & PROXIMITY: Our listings are right in the heart of Costa Mesa and Orange County and conveniently located near Newport Beach, Huntington Beach, Balboa Island, Corona Del Mar, UCI, Disneyland and the main freeways to Los Angeles, San Diego and San Bernardino mountains.

SHARING & PRIVACY:  This is a shared home so we live on the property and we can have multiple guests at one time. All the guests have their private rooms and private spaces as well as access to the two bathrooms and communal areas. Please click on our profile to see our other listings. We also help with co-hosting. 

CLEANLINESS:

As we have multiple guests, two well mannered rambunctious growing boys ( 14 and 11 years old) and a busy schedule, our house won’t be immaculate like a hotel at all times. You will see our personal belongings in the communal areas and in our own rooms. However, you are assured that we make every effort to ensure your rooms are cleaned and made with fresh & crisp bedding & the bathrooms are attended frequently. 

HOMESTAY VS HOTEL EXPECTATIONS:

You will be staying in a Homestay, means that this is our home in which we are renting out private rooms and spaces to our guests so yes, you will be sharing with other people including us the hosts. On average, there will be 4 of us and there may be 3 or 4 more people depending how many are booked in our 2 other rooms and backyard facilities. 

We are attentive and love to ensure our guests needs are met so we will respond to your requests as soon as we are available. If we don’t meet any of your 5 star expectations, please bring to our attention immediately so we can address it sooner than later. We want to be your 5 star hosts, we really do!

If you want your own bathroom, don’t like meeting people or have expectations of a hotel, our place may not be the best fit for you.

If you love meeting people, exploring local attractions, enjoy our hospitality and don’t mind sharing the bathrooms with others, you are in right place:-). 

Looking forward to hosting you! 

Thơ & Row Costa Mesa
