I've always had a gift and love for hospitality with a lot of warmth and heart. A dear friend (godsend!) introduced me to hosting and it was match made in heaven! It's been a joy to be a part of our airbnb family.

I'm a former licensed Child and Family Specialist/Marriage Family Therapist turned entrepreneur and coach, love meeting new people, travel, food and swapping recipes, spoiling my very cute rescue netherland dwarf bunnies (Nugget & Daisy Mae), classical music, and creating connections and community where I go. 

I hope you feel at home in our listings and thanks for the joy of hosting you, your friends and family :)!

Warmest regards, 

Lida

host_about:
I've been in sales and marketing all of my life.  I began my career in international sales which allowed me to travel to many countries such as Brazil, Egypt, Japan, the Czech Republic and Vietnam.  I've learned about so many different cultures which has given me so much appreciation for discovering and traveling to new countries around the world.  

I'm a single dad and I have a daughter who is pursuing a career in sports medicine at the University of San Francisco.  She would like to be a doctor some day!  I'm super proud of all of her accomplishments. I know she will go far! 

I'm a foodie, love to try new things and I would love to take my daughter with me around the world when she graduates from college! I am at the gym daily to stay in shape and I eat as healthy as I possibly can, however, I do like to splurge on Baskin-Robbins, cheesecake or a  hearty Chicago style deep-dish pizza every now and then! 

It's very nice to meet you here!  I look forward to hosting you!

name: 🥰 A Sail⛵️ Rm w Queen Bed & semi en-suite bathroom
host_about:
A BIG WELCOME TO OUR HOME OF SUN, SAND, SURF, SAIL & SEA! 

We hope this will be your home away from home for you when you stay with us.  Our reviews speak for us:-).

MEET YOUR HOSTS: 

We are an Australian Vietnamese American family of 4 who have been enjoying hosting our guests from all over the world in our homes for 17 years. We have been Airbnb hosts since 2012 and Superhost since the program started. We were also awarded Outstanding Travelers’ Award by other platforms since 2019. Booking guests rated us as high as 9.1/10 and even higher that some five star hotels in the area. We genuinely love people and we are world travelers who believe that hosting and traveling will open people’s hearts, minds & souls and ultimately make the world a better place. 

ABOUT COSTA MESA: Do you know that Costa Mesa is the City of the Art & home for Orange County’s top rated restaurants? It’s a mecca for foodies, adventures seekers and fun loving families. The amenities are top notch and all are within 10-20 minute walk or drive.

LOCATION & PROXIMITY: Our listings are right in the heart of Costa Mesa and Orange County and conveniently located near Newport Beach, Huntington Beach, Balboa Island, Corona Del Mar, UCI, Disneyland and the main freeways to Los Angeles, San Diego and San Bernardino mountains.

SHARING & PRIVACY:  This is a shared home so we live on the property and we can have multiple guests at one time. All the guests have their private rooms and private spaces as well as access to the two bathrooms and communal areas. Please click on our profile to see our other listings. We also help with co-hosting. 

CLEANLINESS:

As we have multiple guests, two well mannered rambunctious growing boys ( 14 and 11 years old) and a busy schedule, our house won’t be immaculate like a hotel at all times. You will see our personal belongings in the communal areas and in our own rooms. However, you are assured that we make every effort to ensure your rooms are cleaned and made with fresh & crisp bedding & the bathrooms are attended frequently. 

HOMESTAY VS HOTEL EXPECTATIONS:

You will be staying in a Homestay, means that this is our home in which we are renting out private rooms and spaces to our guests so yes, you will be sharing with other people including us the hosts. On average, there will be 4 of us and there may be 3 or 4 more people depending how many are booked in our 2 other rooms and backyard facilities. 

We are attentive and love to ensure our guests needs are met so we will respond to your requests as soon as we are available. If we don’t meet any of your 5 star expectations, please bring to our attention immediately so we can address it sooner than later. We want to be your 5 star hosts, we really do!

If you want your own bathroom, don’t like meeting people or have expectations of a hotel, our place may not be the best fit for you.

If you love meeting people, exploring local attractions, enjoy our hospitality and don’t mind sharing the bathrooms with others, you are in right place:-). 

Looking forward to hosting you! 

Thơ & Row Costa Mesa

Happy Bookings!

name: Spacious EnSuite King Bedroom near Malibu!
host_about:
Nico is a Lifestyle Guide and Gratitude Activist!

Her journey has taken her from a quirky upbringing in small town New Jersey, to a home base in Harlem while butlering around the world. She left it all on a one-way ticket to Bali, in search to find not how much she could have, but how much she could offer. 

She is the Founder of Agape Everyday, a 5-min gratitude mediation, recently ranked in the top 3% of Apple Podcasts. Bali offered her a place to call home for 3-years, guiding yoga and meditation to all groups, from nudists in her treehouse to orphanages in the villages and bringing water filters to those in need.

Her current work bridges the gap between Eastern philosophies and Western lifestyles, creating value through awareness of all that is present.

Her biggest passions include reading, writing, cooking for friends, yoga on the patio and hosting amazing guests in her California mountain home.

name: *SANITIZED*Bungalow Zen 2BD/2BA | Cozy & Spacious
host_about:
Hi! My name is Isabella and I am a first generation German American. I grew up in Torrance, California, graduated from UC Berkeley with a degree in English (after a degree in Fashion Design and later a Master's Degree in Holistic Nutrition). Hosting you brings all of my passions together: wellness, design, and meditation! My goal is for you to not only have everything you need to enjoy your vacation, but also to have a space for meditation and personal growth. 

I lived in Germany for 4 years (in Munich and Cologne) and had the opportunity to see and experience many different hotels and bed and breakfasts. My goal is to think of the details so you don't have to. 

I created this Zen space with a select guest in mind who enjoys meditation and elevating their energy with a mindful space. Salt lamps, Organic Coffee and Green Tea, and Organic Towels will make you feel relaxed and cocooned. 

I hope you have a Zen experience!
